WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.000
- Ibrahim X : @sle1i

2
00:00:15.083 --> 00:00:25.083
Street-talk translation

3
00:00:33.666 --> 00:00:34.833
One face!

4
00:00:37.833 --> 00:00:39.083
One fleet!

5
00:00:42.083 --> 00:00:43.083
One war!

6
00:00:46.916 --> 00:00:47.916
One man!

7
00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:51.833
One thought!

8
00:00:55.250 --> 00:00:56.250
One trick!

9
00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:01.833
A scheme to break into Troy!

10
00:01:04.083 --> 00:01:06.916
And torch it. wreck it
while they're screaming!

11
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

12
00:01:58.750 --> 00:02:00.250
What's the play here?

13
00:02:08.916 --> 00:02:10.083
A gift

14
00:02:13.333 --> 00:02:14.750
for Athena.

15
00:02:17.916 --> 00:02:19.166
We vibe with the same gods.

16
00:02:19.916 --> 00:02:21.416
show some respect
for their present.

17
00:02:25.583 --> 00:02:26.583
Drag that thing
out of the water!

18
00:02:27.166 --> 00:02:29.083
Take it to Athena's temple.

19
00:02:29.750 --> 00:02:31.333
The war's done.

20
00:02:39.166 --> 00:02:40.250
Face!

21
00:02:43.416 --> 00:02:44.583
Fleet!

22
00:02:47.083 --> 00:02:48.166
War!

23
00:02:51.500 --> 00:02:52.583
Man!

24
00:02:53.166 --> 00:02:54.166
Cut it out!

25
00:02:58.916 --> 00:02:59.916
Not that song.

26
00:03:04.916 --> 00:03:06.333
Mama's boy!

27
00:03:07.500 --> 00:03:09.416
Run. kid.

28
00:03:10.083 --> 00:03:11.166
run!

29
00:03:12.250 --> 00:03:14.583
Just reminding them
who owns this wine.

30
00:03:14.750 --> 00:03:17.666
I don't need a song about
Odysseus. I want the man himself.

31
00:03:17.916 --> 00:03:20.750
And you're really letting these thirsty
dudes crash at his place every night?

32
00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:23.166
In this day and age.

33
00:03:23.750 --> 00:03:27.000
a guy does what he wants. and
I'm just doing what I can.

34
00:03:27.416 --> 00:03:29.833
I'm a man now. Mom.

35
00:03:30.416 --> 00:03:32.083
Then kick them out.

36
00:03:32.666 --> 00:03:36.083
break Zeus's rules. give
them an excuse to jump you.

37
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
I already lost one husband.

38
00:03:44.666 --> 00:03:46.250
I'm not losing my son too.

39
00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:49.166
Dad's coming back.
- Where's he at?

40
00:03:49.583 --> 00:03:52.083
It's been eight years
since Troy fell.

41
00:03:52.333 --> 00:03:54.333
and like twenty years
since he dipped.

42
00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:55.750
Where is he?

43
00:04:06.583 --> 00:04:08.916
He's a guest here.
same as you guys.

44
00:04:09.083 --> 00:04:10.333
You calling us beggars?

45
00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:12.833
I'm saying we've been putting
up with you for three years now.

46
00:04:13.166 --> 00:04:16.166
We're overstaying our welcome.

47
00:04:17.583 --> 00:04:19.166
only 'cause your mom
won't make a move.

48
00:04:19.666 --> 00:04:22.250
She's already hitched.
- Odysseus is toast.

49
00:04:22.916 --> 00:04:24.666
What do you know about my dad?

50
00:04:27.166 --> 00:04:30.000
That his meat is tough
and his wine is trash.

51
00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:32.500
You've been drinking the good
stuff for two years straight.

52
00:04:32.583 --> 00:04:34.166
I know he hasn't shown up.

53
00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:35.500
Not yet.

54
00:04:37.166 --> 00:04:39.083
You're crying for a dad

55
00:04:39.250 --> 00:04:40.583
you never even knew.

56
00:04:40.916 --> 00:04:42.666
like a total loser.

57
00:04:43.083 --> 00:04:45.666
Nobody's ever 100%
sure who their dad is.

58
00:04:45.833 --> 00:04:47.250
You can't even be
sure about mine.

59
00:04:47.500 --> 00:04:48.500
I knew him.

60
00:04:48.916 --> 00:04:51.333
We grew up watching him hunt.

61
00:04:53.333 --> 00:04:55.333
I signed up for Troy.

62
00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:56.916
He told me to stay put.

63
00:04:57.083 --> 00:04:58.250
and look after you.

64
00:04:59.583 --> 00:05:00.583
But.

65
00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:03.916
Sparta's crawling
with Troy vets.

66
00:05:04.166 --> 00:05:05.833
it's a goldmine for intel.

67
00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:07.833
You really Odysseus's kid?

68
00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:09.500
Head to Sparta.

69
00:05:09.916 --> 00:05:12.000
find Menelaus.

70
00:05:12.666 --> 00:05:13.666
He'll talk to you.

71
00:05:15.750 --> 00:05:18.083
The queen wants a
word with the new guy.

72
00:05:19.250 --> 00:05:20.750
She's thirsty for the tea.

73
00:05:23.666 --> 00:05:25.083
But don't get her hopes up.

74
00:05:25.333 --> 00:05:28.083
She's got a vibe for knowing if
anyone's actually seen Odysseus.

75
00:05:28.583 --> 00:05:29.583
You see this guy?

76
00:05:30.083 --> 00:05:31.666
He's basically blind.

77
00:05:31.833 --> 00:05:33.666
but he'll wreck anyone

78
00:05:33.916 --> 00:05:36.000
who lies about my dad.

79
00:06:03.583 --> 00:06:04.583
Too fast.

80
00:06:05.333 --> 00:06:06.333
How do you know?

81
00:06:06.583 --> 00:06:10.000
You don't need eyes to
hear a sloppy combo.

82
00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:11.583
Mentor. go harder on him.

83
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:21.166
Too fast.

84
00:06:30.833 --> 00:06:32.666
He's as chill as you are!

85
00:06:33.333 --> 00:06:35.250
He only listened to your dad.

86
00:06:35.666 --> 00:06:37.000
Where'd he even find this guy?

87
00:06:37.666 --> 00:06:39.166
They linked up here.

88
00:06:48.583 --> 00:06:50.833
I'll take it.
- For your kid?

89
00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:52.750
For hunting.

90
00:06:54.333 --> 00:06:55.416
He had a good eye.

91
00:07:31.833 --> 00:07:32.916
Stay still.

92
00:07:33.083 --> 00:07:35.083
You want a nasty scar?

93
00:07:37.166 --> 00:07:39.416
Why do you make the string snap?
- It's fair.

94
00:07:39.750 --> 00:07:42.416
To give the prey a
heads-up? To keep it fair.

95
00:07:42.666 --> 00:07:44.500
You weren't sparring.
you were hunting.

96
00:07:44.750 --> 00:07:46.583
Hunting's just a
fight in disguise.

97
00:07:47.166 --> 00:07:51.000
Smooth. but your games are
gonna get you in trouble.

98
00:07:51.250 --> 00:07:52.250
Try again.

99
00:07:52.916 --> 00:07:55.250
less panic. more focus.

100
00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:57.916
You aren't winning just
by playing defense.

101
00:07:58.166 --> 00:07:59.166
Bait him into swinging.

102
00:07:59.416 --> 00:08:01.166
How? Hesitate.

103
00:08:01.833 --> 00:08:05.666
Leave yourself wide open.
His own attack will be his L.

104
00:08:38.416 --> 00:08:40.083
Did you teach my dad that?

105
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.583
He taught me that.

106
00:08:42.833 --> 00:08:43.833
One.

107
00:08:43.916 --> 00:08:46.916
"You won't always be the
biggest or the fastest.

108
00:08:47.166 --> 00:08:49.166
so be the smartest."

109
00:08:49.916 --> 00:08:51.250
What would he do

110
00:08:51.833 --> 00:08:54.000
if he saw these
losers in his house?

111
00:08:54.166 --> 00:08:57.000
I can't even wrap my head
around what he'd do to them.

112
00:08:57.250 --> 00:08:58.583
There's just so many of them.

113
00:08:58.750 --> 00:09:00.833
You take out two and
the rest will fold.

114
00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:02.583
these fake tough guys.

115
00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:06.083
They were supposed to head to Troy.
but when Agamemnon came knocking.

116
00:09:09.916 --> 00:09:11.166
their dads hid them away.

117
00:09:14.583 --> 00:09:19.166
He knew Agamemnon's war would
be a long. deadly grind.

118
00:09:23.666 --> 00:09:25.583
So he picked his crew
by drawing straws.

119
00:09:28.333 --> 00:09:29.416
Name? Sinon.

120
00:09:29.750 --> 00:09:31.166
Draw.
- Nah.

121
00:09:31.416 --> 00:09:32.500
Name?
- Antinous.

122
00:09:32.666 --> 00:09:33.750
Draw.

123
00:09:35.250 --> 00:09:36.250
Bet.

124
00:09:36.416 --> 00:09:37.583
By drawing straws?

125
00:09:39.833 --> 00:09:41.916
Antinous claims he
signed up for it.

126
00:09:42.166 --> 00:09:43.666
They're plotting something.

127
00:09:51.750 --> 00:09:53.666
Your son wants to sub for Sinon.

128
00:09:54.750 --> 00:09:56.000
No way.

129
00:09:56.166 --> 00:09:57.916
He's staying put for his family.

130
00:10:00.916 --> 00:10:03.500
He'll watch out for
your kid too. Obviously.

131
00:10:08.416 --> 00:10:08.750
He's coming with me.

132
00:10:09.083 --> 00:10:11.000
He wanted Antinous
to babysit me?

133
00:10:12.416 --> 00:10:15.083
Odysseus wanted to save
those dads from the shame.

134
00:10:15.333 --> 00:10:17.000
he felt for them.

135
00:10:17.583 --> 00:10:20.000
He loved your mom and
you more than any clout.

136
00:10:21.583 --> 00:10:23.583
He knew this would
be a long haul.

137
00:10:24.333 --> 00:10:25.666
Did he tell my mom?

138
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.083
- Ask her.
- Eumaeus...

139
00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:30.833
Is he ever coming back?

140
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:33.333
Argos thinks so.

141
00:10:33.583 --> 00:10:36.166
I've never seen a
dog hit 20 years.

142
00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:39.416
He's been holding on
long after his owner.

143
00:10:56.166 --> 00:10:57.750
My bad for cutting in.

144
00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:02.833
I'm in no rush.

145
00:11:03.583 --> 00:11:07.083
According to the OGs. once I
finish your grandpa's shroud.

146
00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:08.583
I gotta get remarried.

147
00:11:08.750 --> 00:11:09.750
Why?

148
00:11:15.583 --> 00:11:17.666
Ithaca's still got no king.

149
00:11:18.416 --> 00:11:19.833
They want some protection.

150
00:11:20.083 --> 00:11:21.083
From who?

151
00:11:21.333 --> 00:11:22.750
From the Sea People.

152
00:11:23.166 --> 00:11:25.500
Those are just campfire stories.

153
00:11:25.750 --> 00:11:29.500
Travelers spill tea about the
world and the fall of Troy.

154
00:11:30.166 --> 00:11:33.583
and they're all talkin' about
these Sea People attacks.

155
00:11:34.666 --> 00:11:36.666
Who even are these Sea People?

156
00:11:36.833 --> 00:11:39.916
Nobody knows. but the Elders
are tryna get us ready.

157
00:11:40.083 --> 00:11:41.166
Ready for what?

158
00:11:41.333 --> 00:11:44.666
Our spot is the
GOAT. for real.

159
00:11:45.833 --> 00:11:47.666
Look at this massive crib.

160
00:11:47.833 --> 00:11:49.500
these old-school stones.

161
00:11:49.916 --> 00:11:53.166
just sitting here for these
greedy deadbeats to mess with.

162
00:11:53.916 --> 00:11:55.833
The building is whatever.

163
00:11:56.416 --> 00:11:58.250
if you ignore what it
actually stands for.

164
00:11:58.833 --> 00:12:00.000
Zeus's law.

165
00:12:01.083 --> 00:12:03.083
Treating people right.

166
00:12:03.583 --> 00:12:06.333
They're just trashing it
and ruining everything.

167
00:12:06.916 --> 00:12:09.166
How could you even think about
marrying one of those losers?

168
00:12:09.500 --> 00:12:11.750
Because that was
a long time ago.

169
00:12:13.083 --> 00:12:14.916
Your dad asked me to.

170
00:12:15.333 --> 00:12:16.916
Agamemnon is the king.

171
00:12:17.583 --> 00:12:21.666
The Trojans snatched his sister-in-law.
- Or she just dipped with them.

172
00:12:21.916 --> 00:12:26.083
Either way. people think the walls
of Troy are impossible to break.

173
00:12:26.583 --> 00:12:29.000
We're gonna camp right
outside that city.

174
00:12:29.166 --> 00:12:31.666
and dare them to come
out and throw hands.

175
00:12:33.416 --> 00:12:36.416
And the years will fly by.
Telemachus will get older.

176
00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.250
and you'll learn how to
handle things without me.

177
00:12:39.416 --> 00:12:42.000
Menelaus is gonna
give up on Helen.

178
00:12:46.750 --> 00:12:48.583
This is just Agamemnon's excuse

179
00:12:48.750 --> 00:12:52.333
to mess with Troy's hold
on all the trade routes.

180
00:12:54.083 --> 00:12:56.083
He's not backing down.

181
00:12:56.583 --> 00:12:57.750
Never.

182
00:13:04.083 --> 00:13:06.250
And what if you say no?

183
00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:13.250
He'll snatch our son.

184
00:13:14.916 --> 00:13:16.166
He wouldn't.

185
00:13:16.583 --> 00:13:18.250
He literally
sacrificed his own kid

186
00:13:18.416 --> 00:13:20.666
just to get some good wind.

187
00:13:21.416 --> 00:13:24.000
Did the gods actually
ask for her life?

188
00:13:24.333 --> 00:13:26.416
A sacrifice's power

189
00:13:27.583 --> 00:13:30.250
comes from what it costs
the person doing it.

190
00:13:33.250 --> 00:13:34.916
That's messed up.

191
00:13:37.416 --> 00:13:38.916
And heartless.

192
00:13:41.750 --> 00:13:43.833
I won't be back anytime soon.

193
00:13:44.333 --> 00:13:45.750
if I even make it back at all.

194
00:13:49.916 --> 00:13:51.250
What if we just ran away?

195
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:55.916
With your fastest ship
and your best crew.

196
00:13:56.666 --> 00:13:58.500
we'd head for the horizon.

197
00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:01.916
hand in hand.

198
00:14:02.166 --> 00:14:04.083
sailing west at sunset.

199
00:14:04.333 --> 00:14:06.000
chasing the sun.

200
00:14:09.666 --> 00:14:11.833
There's a whole world out there.

201
00:14:12.250 --> 00:14:14.333
Agamemnon's revenge

202
00:14:15.750 --> 00:14:17.916
would come for Ithaca.

203
00:14:23.583 --> 00:14:24.916
Do me a favor.

204
00:14:26.750 --> 00:14:28.333
If I'm not back

205
00:14:28.833 --> 00:14:30.666
by the time Telemachus is grown.

206
00:14:31.583 --> 00:14:32.750
promise me

207
00:14:34.333 --> 00:14:35.916
you'll find someone else.

208
00:14:38.166 --> 00:14:39.250
No more sacrifices.

209
00:14:39.666 --> 00:14:41.000
Love isn't a sacrifice.

210
00:14:41.250 --> 00:14:42.500
Yeah. it totally is.

211
00:14:43.583 --> 00:14:44.833
I just don't want you
to deal with that.

212
00:14:45.083 --> 00:14:46.500
That's not your call.

213
00:14:48.750 --> 00:14:50.083
Promise me.

214
00:14:56.166 --> 00:14:58.000
And you promise me
you'll come back.

215
00:15:03.166 --> 00:15:04.666
What if I can't?

216
00:15:10.166 --> 00:15:13.083
Then I'm not gonna let your
ghost make my choices for me.

217
00:15:17.666 --> 00:15:18.833
Take my brooch.

218
00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:23.000
keep it on you always and
Athena will get you home.

219
00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:25.166
I don't think that's my style.

220
00:15:27.416 --> 00:15:29.583
If travelers say they saw you.

221
00:15:29.750 --> 00:15:31.500
I'm gonna ask what
you were wearing

222
00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:33.166
and I'll know if
they're capping.

223
00:15:36.416 --> 00:15:38.750
If the Sea People
are actually real.

224
00:15:39.583 --> 00:15:43.083
Ithaca is totally screwed without
a king to lead the charge.

225
00:15:43.750 --> 00:15:45.083
I can step up.

226
00:15:47.416 --> 00:15:48.416
Come on.

227
00:16:00.583 --> 00:16:01.583
Pull the string.

228
00:16:12.416 --> 00:16:13.916
That's not fair!

229
00:16:14.333 --> 00:16:16.500
You always say only
he could do it.

230
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:18.750
He let other people try.

231
00:16:20.916 --> 00:16:22.500
He lined up the axes...

232
00:16:56.416 --> 00:16:58.333
Nobody else has pulled it off.

233
00:16:59.250 --> 00:17:00.750
They're straight up ruining us.

234
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:04.833
so you'll marry one of them
before I can take the crown.

235
00:17:05.250 --> 00:17:07.833
Menelaus came back ages ago.

236
00:17:08.583 --> 00:17:11.416
Everyone came back.
- Only the ones who survived!

237
00:17:12.750 --> 00:17:14.500
Maybe he's dead.

238
00:17:14.750 --> 00:17:16.833
Then this palace would be mine.

239
00:17:18.083 --> 00:17:19.083
We gotta know for sure.

240
00:17:19.250 --> 00:17:21.833
and I have to hit up
Menelaus to find out.

241
00:17:22.083 --> 00:17:25.750
Telemachus. those
guys are bad news.

242
00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:28.083
You think I don't know that?

243
00:17:28.416 --> 00:17:31.083
Every night they're tryna
bait me into messing up.

244
00:17:31.250 --> 00:17:34.416
And out there. on the
water or the road.

245
00:17:35.166 --> 00:17:37.416
they won't even need
an excuse to end you!

246
00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:42.000
You don't want me to lead.

247
00:17:44.083 --> 00:17:48.166
You just want to keep me in my place
so you can stay queen of Ithaca.

248
00:17:48.333 --> 00:17:51.000
I'm sick of being a
queen without my man!

249
00:17:51.416 --> 00:17:52.750
Without your man?

250
00:17:54.166 --> 00:17:55.166
Or just without a king?

251
00:17:56.916 --> 00:18:00.250
And you think you're ready
to fill your dad's shoes?

252
00:18:01.916 --> 00:18:03.333
You're just a kid.

253
00:18:14.166 --> 00:18:16.000
Keep it down. Melanthius.

254
00:18:16.166 --> 00:18:20.166
Lose the spurs in the house.
You're a cowherd. not a rider.

255
00:18:20.333 --> 00:18:23.916
And you're just a pig guy. Who gave
you the right to talk to me like that?

256
00:18:24.083 --> 00:18:28.000
Our boss put me in
charge of the shepherds.

257
00:18:28.166 --> 00:18:31.916
We haven't had a boss in
forever. you old blind geezer.

258
00:18:32.083 --> 00:18:34.750
and you're just as
unwelcome here as this mutt.

259
00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:37.083
Argos.

260
00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:46.083
Argos.

261
00:18:47.500 --> 00:18:49.166
Boss. he didn't do anything.

262
00:18:49.416 --> 00:18:50.750
So you're the one who reeks?

263
00:18:52.166 --> 00:18:53.416
Leave the old dog alone.

264
00:18:53.916 --> 00:18:55.416
Which one?
- Both of us.

265
00:18:56.750 --> 00:18:57.750
You tryna throw shade at me?

266
00:18:57.916 --> 00:19:00.583
You really wanted to save
my dad's hunting dog?

267
00:19:00.750 --> 00:19:02.000
A hunting dog?

268
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.333
Look at this trash.

269
00:19:08.416 --> 00:19:09.750
Get it out. We're tryna eat.

270
00:19:09.916 --> 00:19:11.583
Can't you see he's in pain?

271
00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:14.083
Then let me put him
out of his misery.

272
00:19:14.250 --> 00:19:15.250
Back off!

273
00:19:32.916 --> 00:19:33.916
Did you see that?

274
00:19:35.166 --> 00:19:36.166
Did y'all see that?

275
00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:40.250
He jumped me! I'm
in the right here!

276
00:19:40.916 --> 00:19:41.916
Chill!

277
00:19:44.416 --> 00:19:46.333
Don't mess with my kid.

278
00:19:49.083 --> 00:19:50.833
Take it easy. Polybus.

279
00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:53.666
The kid just got
heated. have some mercy.

280
00:19:56.083 --> 00:19:58.416
Keep drinking his
wine. I'll handle it.

281
00:19:59.083 --> 00:20:00.833
This is my dad's hunting dog.

282
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:04.416
He's only hanging on to
see Odysseus come back.

283
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:08.833
I'll toss him on the trash heap
outside. so he can see him a bit sooner.

284
00:20:18.583 --> 00:20:20.666
The dog stays outside!

285
00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:24.916
Don't be dumb and throw
your life away for a dog.

286
00:20:36.083 --> 00:20:37.166
Eurycleia.

287
00:20:39.416 --> 00:20:41.666
get some food to the ships

288
00:20:41.916 --> 00:20:43.083
using people we
can actually trust.

289
00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:44.583
This is gonna destroy your mom.

290
00:20:44.833 --> 00:20:48.166
If I stay. I'll have to
fight and I've got no backup.

291
00:20:48.416 --> 00:20:50.166
I need info on my dad.

292
00:20:50.416 --> 00:20:53.583
Ithaca will back me if
Odysseus is for sure dead.

293
00:20:53.833 --> 00:20:56.750
The suitors are gonna go
berserk. you're not coming back!

294
00:20:56.916 --> 00:21:00.000
Tell Mentor to get to the
ships before the sun comes up.

295
00:21:00.166 --> 00:21:02.833
What do you want me
to tell your mom?

296
00:21:03.833 --> 00:21:05.666
To hold it down as
long as she can.

297
00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:11.416
The ship is good to
go. the tide is right.

298
00:21:11.750 --> 00:21:15.333
Did I ever tell you that you've got
the eyes of a genius. like Athena?

299
00:21:15.500 --> 00:21:16.500
Once or twice.

300
00:21:16.833 --> 00:21:18.500
Aren't you gonna ask
where we're headed?

301
00:21:18.833 --> 00:21:21.250
Where are we headed?
- To find my dad.

302
00:21:21.500 --> 00:21:24.166
He's still alive. I
can feel it in the air.

303
00:21:24.416 --> 00:21:27.666
He's out there somewhere.
hurt. ghosting. who even knows?

304
00:21:29.083 --> 00:21:30.416
But he's alive.

305
00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:02.166
Tripping on dreams again?

306
00:22:03.416 --> 00:22:05.000
People drowning

307
00:22:05.583 --> 00:22:08.416
in some

308
00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:10.916
dark AF place.

309
00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:16.083
Firelight hitting the
stone. My bad. I spaced out.

310
00:22:18.416 --> 00:22:19.416
On purpose?

311
00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:23.166
Why do the gods have to
be so extra and confusing?

312
00:22:25.333 --> 00:22:27.416
Who doesn't get thunder?

313
00:22:27.916 --> 00:22:29.166
Or fire?

314
00:22:29.666 --> 00:22:32.416
A kid's smile. a good
vibe for the crops?

315
00:22:32.666 --> 00:22:34.666
You're dodging us.

316
00:22:36.416 --> 00:22:37.500
Peep this.

317
00:22:38.500 --> 00:22:40.250
Who's moving that cloud?

318
00:22:40.916 --> 00:22:42.833
Who's rounding up those birds?

319
00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:45.666
Who's messing with the water?

320
00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:48.833
Who were you chatting with?

321
00:22:51.833 --> 00:22:53.416
Athena hit me up again.

322
00:22:54.166 --> 00:22:56.250
She's telling me
to keep it real.

323
00:22:57.916 --> 00:23:00.083
To bounce.
- Why bounce?

324
00:23:00.833 --> 00:23:02.583
We've got everything
we need right here.

325
00:23:03.500 --> 00:23:06.083
How long have I been
stuck here. Calypso?

326
00:23:10.166 --> 00:23:12.416
I've got a home out
there somewhere.

327
00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:15.166
I've got someone

328
00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:17.083
in the real world.

329
00:23:17.583 --> 00:23:18.750
How would you know?

330
00:23:19.416 --> 00:23:20.666
I don't.

331
00:23:23.250 --> 00:23:24.416
I just feel it.

332
00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:43.083
This life could last forever.

333
00:23:43.333 --> 00:23:44.583
That's a god thing.
not a me thing.

334
00:23:44.750 --> 00:23:46.333
You a goddess or something?

335
00:23:49.166 --> 00:23:52.833
You want to remember? What if
the memories just kill your vibe?

336
00:23:53.250 --> 00:23:54.833
Then it was all fake anyway.

337
00:24:04.166 --> 00:24:06.000
Stop snacking on those.
- But they're fire.

338
00:24:06.750 --> 00:24:08.000
No more lotus snacks.

339
00:24:08.416 --> 00:24:10.416
What do you actually remember?

340
00:24:11.916 --> 00:24:12.916
Back after Troy.

341
00:24:15.250 --> 00:24:16.583
Troy?

342
00:24:22.750 --> 00:24:24.166
We crushed that war.

343
00:24:24.750 --> 00:24:26.083
And then?

344
00:25:34.250 --> 00:25:36.000
Ten years stuck on
this trash shore.

345
00:25:41.750 --> 00:25:43.083
We're going home. baby!

346
00:25:44.583 --> 00:25:46.583
Don't forget the homies
we're leaving behind.

347
00:25:51.250 --> 00:25:53.166
We got enough supplies?

348
00:25:53.666 --> 00:25:55.666
We looted enough from Troy.

349
00:25:56.250 --> 00:25:58.500
A pit stop or two won't hurt.

350
00:26:10.250 --> 00:26:11.250
Pull the oars in.

351
00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:12.500
Chill out!

352
00:26:13.666 --> 00:26:14.833
Get the oars in!

353
00:26:20.916 --> 00:26:23.583
We're popping the sail and
catching the south wind.

354
00:26:25.166 --> 00:26:27.833
Agamemnon is rowing
toward the west side.

355
00:26:28.000 --> 00:26:29.666
Too many mouths to feed.

356
00:26:29.833 --> 00:26:31.033
We'll find a spot to dock.

357
00:26:31.166 --> 00:26:32.250
That's sketchy.

358
00:26:32.500 --> 00:26:34.000
I'm done following
Agamemnon's lead.

359
00:26:34.916 --> 00:26:37.083
With a little luck
and some wind.

360
00:26:37.250 --> 00:26:40.666
we'll see some of the world
and beat Agamemnon home.

361
00:27:46.916 --> 00:27:48.833
Keep the Big Dipper
to your right.

362
00:27:57.666 --> 00:27:58.666
Odysseus!

363
00:27:58.833 --> 00:28:00.000
Land ho!

364
00:28:03.083 --> 00:28:04.166
See that?

365
00:28:04.583 --> 00:28:06.000
Lucky you.

366
00:28:06.583 --> 00:28:08.000
Our food stash was running low.

367
00:28:08.166 --> 00:28:09.500
Send a crew to the beach

368
00:28:09.666 --> 00:28:11.750
and ask for three weeks of grub.

369
00:28:12.000 --> 00:28:13.166
What if they say no?

370
00:28:15.083 --> 00:28:16.916
You in a rush to
get home or what?

371
00:28:17.583 --> 00:28:19.250
Get your gear ready!

372
00:28:19.416 --> 00:28:21.583
To ask. to trade.

373
00:28:22.416 --> 00:28:23.583
or to just take it.

374
00:28:26.916 --> 00:28:30.500
Why'd they ghost the village
instead of just saying hey?

375
00:28:36.583 --> 00:28:39.083
They thought we
were the Sea People.

376
00:28:39.583 --> 00:28:42.000
We're just Greeks from Ithaca.

377
00:28:42.916 --> 00:28:45.333
Maybe they know we wrecked Troy.

378
00:28:45.916 --> 00:28:47.916
We're rolling with
the south wind.

379
00:28:55.166 --> 00:28:56.333
If we stay on this path.

380
00:28:57.166 --> 00:28:59.333
we're not gonna
like what we find.

381
00:29:00.416 --> 00:29:02.416
After years of straight war.

382
00:29:03.250 --> 00:29:05.833
nobody was stopping my crew

383
00:29:06.083 --> 00:29:07.250
from getting back home.

384
00:29:08.250 --> 00:29:09.750
Not even me.

385
00:29:10.916 --> 00:29:12.666
Did something go down there?

386
00:29:29.833 --> 00:29:31.583
Chasing the sun. man.

387
00:29:32.083 --> 00:29:33.083
Land!

388
00:29:36.666 --> 00:29:37.916
Here we go.

389
00:29:40.833 --> 00:29:42.166
Super lucky.

390
00:29:57.083 --> 00:29:59.333
Sheep hang in herds.

391
00:30:00.750 --> 00:30:01.750
Let's tail them.

392
00:31:25.416 --> 00:31:26.916
Someone's living here.

393
00:31:27.833 --> 00:31:29.000
And making cheese.

394
00:31:47.333 --> 00:31:48.666
This stuff is delicious!

395
00:31:51.500 --> 00:31:53.583
And there's tons of it!
- Let's bail.

396
00:31:54.333 --> 00:31:55.833
We don't have anything to trade.

397
00:31:56.583 --> 00:31:57.916
Zeus's law. bro.

398
00:31:58.083 --> 00:32:01.333
Does this guy even know about
Zeus's law. or Zeus at all?

399
00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:03.500
Everyone knows Zeus's law.

400
00:32:03.750 --> 00:32:04.833
Keep the fire lit

401
00:32:05.083 --> 00:32:06.833
for when the boss gets back.

402
00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:25.166
Back away from the fire.

403
00:33:29.583 --> 00:33:30.750
Scatter!

404
00:35:03.916 --> 00:35:05.333
I think he's out cold.

405
00:35:51.500 --> 00:35:52.500
Hold up.

406
00:35:56.333 --> 00:35:57.416
The rock.

407
00:36:05.166 --> 00:36:06.333
It's way too heavy.

408
00:36:06.916 --> 00:36:08.500
We're trapped.

409
00:36:16.666 --> 00:36:19.000
Tomorrow morning.

410
00:36:19.333 --> 00:36:21.250
when he lets the animals out.

411
00:36:21.416 --> 00:36:22.833
we bolt for the door.

412
00:36:23.083 --> 00:36:24.166
Catch some Z's.

413
00:37:02.583 --> 00:37:03.750
Let's go!

414
00:37:12.000 --> 00:37:16.416
We could jam something in the
door to keep a crack open.

415
00:37:17.083 --> 00:37:18.250
Maybe.

416
00:37:19.083 --> 00:37:20.500
But what?

417
00:37:20.666 --> 00:37:22.000
This log.

418
00:37:25.583 --> 00:37:27.000
He'll totally see it.

419
00:37:28.583 --> 00:37:31.583
We'll char the thin
end in the fire.

420
00:37:32.083 --> 00:37:33.166
Do we even have...?

421
00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:35.333
How many animals are there?

422
00:37:35.916 --> 00:37:37.083
Like twenty or thirty.

423
00:37:39.500 --> 00:37:40.833
There's too many of us.

424
00:37:41.333 --> 00:37:44.083
On the way out. two
of us go at a time.

425
00:37:44.583 --> 00:37:45.750
Or get wrecked.

426
00:37:50.750 --> 00:37:53.833
Keep your heads down among
the sheep and split up.

427
00:37:54.083 --> 00:37:56.750
So he only grabs one.
- Exactly.

428
00:37:56.916 --> 00:37:59.416
We gotta go out in groups
of four. two by two.

429
00:37:59.583 --> 00:38:01.083
Why risk that?

430
00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:02.500
He ate two dudes already.

431
00:38:02.833 --> 00:38:05.083
He's gonna want two more.

432
00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:07.250
What about the body?
- What do you mean?

433
00:40:07.583 --> 00:40:09.500
Just leave it to rot?

434
00:40:10.333 --> 00:40:12.083
As snacks for this thing?

435
00:40:13.500 --> 00:40:16.000
We gotta pay respects
to our dead. Odysseus.

436
00:40:16.166 --> 00:40:19.583
He died so we could make a break for it.
We'll honor him by getting out of here.

437
00:40:29.583 --> 00:40:31.500
Poseidon. get 'em!

438
00:40:32.833 --> 00:40:34.166
He's talking.

439
00:40:35.333 --> 00:40:37.250
Why didn't he say
anything before?

440
00:40:38.333 --> 00:40:39.916
Do you talk to ants?

441
00:40:41.250 --> 00:40:43.083
Should we try to talk it out?

442
00:40:45.083 --> 00:40:46.916
I think that ship has sailed.

443
00:41:56.833 --> 00:41:58.250
What are you doing?

444
00:43:17.333 --> 00:43:18.583
Row!

445
00:43:19.916 --> 00:43:20.916
Harder!

446
00:43:44.083 --> 00:43:45.833
Why'd you shoot an arrow at him?

447
00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:48.000
That beast took
out good soldiers.

448
00:43:48.250 --> 00:43:49.250
And that beast

449
00:43:49.750 --> 00:43:51.250
was Poseidon's kid.

450
00:43:52.750 --> 00:43:55.500
When we poked his eye
out. he screamed his name.

451
00:43:55.916 --> 00:43:57.000
He was a total monster.

452
00:43:57.250 --> 00:43:59.000
I heard him screaming too.

453
00:43:59.166 --> 00:44:02.583
Will the sea be out to
get us? And the wind?

454
00:44:03.416 --> 00:44:06.000
How are we supposed to get back
if Poseidon's beefing with us?

455
00:44:06.250 --> 00:44:09.250
Stop obsessing over
signs and sacrifices.

456
00:44:11.000 --> 00:44:15.250
How many times since Troy have I seen
you crying and praying to Athena?

457
00:44:15.500 --> 00:44:16.833
Did she not show us some love?

458
00:44:18.333 --> 00:44:19.333
Take this.

459
00:44:22.083 --> 00:44:23.166
Wear it.

460
00:44:23.416 --> 00:44:26.083
in memory of the guys
we couldn't bury.

461
00:44:27.500 --> 00:44:29.250
Help yourself. and the
gods will help you out.

462
00:44:32.833 --> 00:44:33.833
After that.

463
00:44:34.666 --> 00:44:36.916
with every rough
storm or headwind.

464
00:44:37.166 --> 00:44:39.250
the crew felt like
they were cursed.

465
00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:42.833
By the way. where are they?

466
00:44:44.666 --> 00:44:46.916
When are you gonna
let me see them again?

467
00:44:47.416 --> 00:44:50.000
They'd help me remember.

468
00:44:50.166 --> 00:44:52.416
Did I even have a
wife. kids. a son?

469
00:44:52.916 --> 00:44:54.916
How long have I been here?

470
00:44:56.000 --> 00:44:57.000
A long time.

471
00:44:57.916 --> 00:44:59.416
If I have a son.

472
00:45:01.750 --> 00:45:03.083
how old is he?

473
00:45:04.750 --> 00:45:06.500
How do you talk to a king?

474
00:45:06.666 --> 00:45:07.916
Chill. don't worry.

475
00:45:08.083 --> 00:45:11.000
Keep your mouth shut.
and if they ask.

476
00:45:11.416 --> 00:45:13.333
we're just merchants from Crete.

477
00:45:13.500 --> 00:45:15.500
We'll figure out how
to approach the king.

478
00:45:25.083 --> 00:45:26.166
Welcome!

479
00:45:26.416 --> 00:45:28.333
Thanks. Seems like you're
in the middle of...

480
00:45:28.500 --> 00:45:29.583
This way.

481
00:45:34.666 --> 00:45:35.750
Where are you dragging us?

482
00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:38.833
The king insists on
greeting foreigners himself.

483
00:45:59.250 --> 00:46:00.250
Sit.

484
00:46:03.583 --> 00:46:04.583
Not you.

485
00:46:05.916 --> 00:46:06.916
You.

486
00:46:09.750 --> 00:46:12.750
Accept our hospitality
like Zeus wants.

487
00:46:13.083 --> 00:46:15.333
before you go telling
us who you are.

488
00:46:16.250 --> 00:46:17.750
Perfect timing!

489
00:46:17.916 --> 00:46:19.916
We're throwing a party
for my daughter's wedding.

490
00:46:20.083 --> 00:46:22.750
She's off to start
a new life tomorrow.

491
00:46:23.500 --> 00:46:26.333
You don't look like much of a
beggar. Do you know who I am?

492
00:46:28.416 --> 00:46:29.833
I'm Menelaus.

493
00:46:30.083 --> 00:46:33.250
son of Atreus.
Agamemnon's brother.

494
00:46:34.250 --> 00:46:35.666
Helen's husband.

495
00:46:36.250 --> 00:46:37.250
Do you remember who she is?

496
00:46:40.250 --> 00:46:41.250
This face

497
00:46:41.833 --> 00:46:43.750
launched a thousand ships.

498
00:46:45.500 --> 00:46:47.666
Pretty sure there's
barely 500 left.

499
00:46:52.083 --> 00:46:54.666
So many dudes died in
Troy for that face.

500
00:46:55.000 --> 00:46:56.833
All because your brother
was power-hungry.

501
00:46:57.833 --> 00:46:59.500
This one looks familiar.

502
00:47:00.833 --> 00:47:02.000
Ajax.

503
00:47:02.666 --> 00:47:03.666
Patroclus.

504
00:47:04.250 --> 00:47:05.250
Achilles.

505
00:47:05.666 --> 00:47:08.916
I miss them less than
this other warrior.

506
00:47:09.750 --> 00:47:11.750
The smartest of the bunch.

507
00:47:13.833 --> 00:47:16.083
Ten years rotting on that beach.

508
00:47:29.166 --> 00:47:32.750
Sinking and tearing
ourselves up. until one guy

509
00:47:36.250 --> 00:47:37.916
figured it out.

510
00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:40.916
Odysseus.

511
00:47:41.333 --> 00:47:43.083
You know the story of the horse?

512
00:47:46.833 --> 00:47:48.250
Seen it from the inside?

513
00:47:53.250 --> 00:47:54.583
We were stuck in there for days.

514
00:47:56.083 --> 00:47:58.666
crammed in since
the ships dipped.

515
00:48:00.250 --> 00:48:03.833
Odysseus didn't want anyone
to know. not even Sinon.

516
00:48:04.000 --> 00:48:06.250
the soldier we left behind.

517
00:48:11.666 --> 00:48:14.833
The first two high tides.
people were drowning.

518
00:48:20.416 --> 00:48:23.416
We were just sitting
in our own filth.

519
00:48:52.833 --> 00:48:54.083
A gift

520
00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:56.083
for Athena.

521
00:48:58.500 --> 00:48:59.916
We share the same gods.

522
00:49:00.583 --> 00:49:02.083
you gotta respect their gift.

523
00:50:22.083 --> 00:50:23.750
We gotta burn it!

524
00:50:24.250 --> 00:50:25.583
Burn it!

525
00:50:47.250 --> 00:50:48.583
This is a gift for Athena!

526
00:50:57.083 --> 00:50:59.166
This is a gift for Athena!

527
00:53:35.166 --> 00:53:36.250
To the gates!

528
00:53:38.166 --> 00:53:42.000
He waited for a night with no
moon to cover the plains of Troy.

529
00:53:56.083 --> 00:53:57.833
Everyone to the gates!

530
00:53:58.666 --> 00:53:59.750
To the gates!

531
00:55:34.750 --> 00:55:36.750
Let's go!

532
00:56:08.250 --> 00:56:09.666
You know the rest.

533
00:56:09.833 --> 00:56:12.750
You moved? You should hear how
the storytellers hype him up.

534
00:56:12.916 --> 00:56:14.166
I've heard them.

535
00:56:17.166 --> 00:56:18.666
They weren't there with you.

536
00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:21.583
With your dad. Odysseus.

537
00:56:24.416 --> 00:56:25.500
You look exactly like him.

538
00:56:26.416 --> 00:56:27.833
Where'd you leave him?

539
00:56:28.166 --> 00:56:29.166
In Troy.

540
00:56:29.583 --> 00:56:31.750
The gods backed our
righteous win...

541
00:56:31.916 --> 00:56:32.916
Righteous?

542
00:56:33.916 --> 00:56:37.500
They backed our win.
but not our trips home.

543
00:56:39.166 --> 00:56:41.500
I made it back after
years. He didn't.

544
00:56:41.666 --> 00:56:43.500
Some people regretted
coming back.

545
00:56:44.416 --> 00:56:45.416
Tell him

546
00:56:45.750 --> 00:56:47.333
what happened to your brother.

547
00:56:47.583 --> 00:56:50.833
The fate the gods had for him
after your "righteous" war.

548
00:56:51.416 --> 00:56:52.833
That he was treated like a hero.

549
00:56:53.000 --> 00:56:55.666
That Agamemnon got
back years before us.

550
00:56:55.833 --> 00:56:59.500
How he was greeted by his
queen. my twin Clytemnestra.

551
00:57:00.583 --> 00:57:01.583
Tell him...

552
00:57:02.000 --> 00:57:04.166
He's not here because
of my brother!

553
00:57:06.416 --> 00:57:07.583
But because of his dad.

554
00:57:08.666 --> 00:57:10.916
I don't know anything
about him since Troy.

555
00:57:11.083 --> 00:57:12.166
Nothing?

556
00:57:13.333 --> 00:57:15.083
Or your people?

557
00:57:15.666 --> 00:57:17.916
Agamemnon's crew.
randoms. merchants?

558
00:57:18.083 --> 00:57:21.166
You just here to collect
gossip and tall tales?

559
00:57:21.750 --> 00:57:23.166
You're in the right
spot for that.

560
00:57:23.583 --> 00:57:26.250
Anyone talking about Odysseus?

561
00:57:26.416 --> 00:57:29.166
They say he's
loaded. he's broke.

562
00:57:30.083 --> 00:57:33.083
or that he's dead. or locked
up. Who's got more info?

563
00:57:33.250 --> 00:57:34.583
Locked up?

564
00:57:37.416 --> 00:57:39.000
What kind of prison

565
00:57:39.666 --> 00:57:41.416
could hold a guy like that?

566
00:57:42.666 --> 00:57:44.833
Tell me what you remember.

567
00:57:45.083 --> 00:57:46.083
The rest will come to you.

568
00:57:47.416 --> 00:57:51.250
The guys kept thinking
I'd pissed off Poseidon.

569
00:58:39.250 --> 00:58:41.333
We made it through
storm after storm.

570
00:58:41.500 --> 00:58:43.666
we got off track

571
00:58:43.833 --> 00:58:45.916
and got totally lost.

572
00:59:40.833 --> 00:59:41.916
Hey.

573
00:59:44.000 --> 00:59:45.083
We come in peace.

574
00:59:48.333 --> 00:59:50.000
We need food.

575
00:59:56.000 --> 00:59:57.083
Food!

576
00:59:59.250 --> 01:00:01.916
Don't you get it?
- He's just a kid.

577
01:00:04.500 --> 01:00:06.833
In that case. what
are his parents like?

578
01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:11.000
Don't trip.

579
01:00:35.000 --> 01:00:36.583
Hurry. back to the ships!

580
01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:23.000
My bow!

581
01:02:40.916 --> 01:02:42.000
Wait.

582
01:02:43.416 --> 01:02:44.666
Row!
- Wait!

583
01:02:52.166 --> 01:02:53.166
Go!

584
01:02:53.333 --> 01:02:54.750
Row!
- Wait!

585
01:03:14.666 --> 01:03:15.666
Let's go!

586
01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:17.750
Get this bucket moving!

587
01:04:12.500 --> 01:04:13.666
Turn left.

588
01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:15.333
stick to the coast.

589
01:04:16.166 --> 01:04:19.083
What if they have ships?
- We gotta bail.

590
01:04:24.333 --> 01:04:27.166
We can't just sail around
blindly with no food.

591
01:04:27.416 --> 01:04:28.916
We're lost.

592
01:04:29.416 --> 01:04:32.500
We need to stock up
and find our way.

593
01:04:35.333 --> 01:04:36.333
To the left.

594
01:05:03.916 --> 01:05:04.916
There!

595
01:05:05.666 --> 01:05:07.083
Smoke!

596
01:05:07.583 --> 01:05:10.583
Follow the shore. we're
beaching the boats!

597
01:05:18.166 --> 01:05:19.500
Oars up!

598
01:05:23.666 --> 01:05:25.416
Send a crew to the beach.

599
01:05:27.750 --> 01:05:29.000
Tomorrow.

600
01:05:31.333 --> 01:05:32.416
Tomorrow.

601
01:05:43.500 --> 01:05:45.333
Leave someone to
watch the boats.

602
01:05:46.833 --> 01:05:48.666
We'd rather you stay.

603
01:05:50.166 --> 01:05:51.166
Us?

604
01:05:51.250 --> 01:05:52.333
All of us.

605
01:05:52.916 --> 01:05:54.166
The ones who made it.

606
01:06:05.500 --> 01:06:06.916
Is this a mutiny?

607
01:06:07.083 --> 01:06:08.416
Figure it out yourself.

608
01:06:13.166 --> 01:06:15.750
Give me the bow. I'll
grab us some food.

609
01:06:16.416 --> 01:06:18.333
even if you come
back with nothing.

610
01:08:01.750 --> 01:08:03.500
Don't trip.

611
01:08:08.583 --> 01:08:10.916
Everything's chill. we
aren't gonna hurt you!

612
01:08:11.250 --> 01:08:12.500
If I bow down to you.

613
01:08:12.750 --> 01:08:15.250
We won't mess with you.

614
01:08:18.666 --> 01:08:20.333
I'm Eurylochus. And you?

615
01:08:20.583 --> 01:08:21.666
Circe.

616
01:08:22.666 --> 01:08:24.333
We need food.

617
01:08:25.416 --> 01:08:26.916
I've got food.

618
01:08:28.416 --> 01:08:29.750
Loads of it.

619
01:08:50.416 --> 01:08:51.833
I'll handle it.

620
01:08:54.583 --> 01:08:56.500
Your weapons and gear.

621
01:08:57.833 --> 01:08:58.833
toss 'em in the back.

622
01:09:40.583 --> 01:09:42.250
You like my stash?

623
01:09:42.833 --> 01:09:45.416
Why you got so much?

624
01:09:46.083 --> 01:09:48.916
Who knows when
randoms might show up?

625
01:09:58.750 --> 01:09:59.750
These guys.

626
01:10:02.916 --> 01:10:04.083
such gluttons.

627
01:10:06.416 --> 01:10:08.666
Never satisfied.

628
01:11:34.833 --> 01:11:36.083
Eurylochus!

629
01:12:02.583 --> 01:12:04.833
They're gone! Anyone here?

630
01:12:05.250 --> 01:12:06.500
Hand over your blade.

631
01:12:10.083 --> 01:12:11.583
Stay by the boats!

632
01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:55.416
C'mon. let's go!

633
01:13:04.416 --> 01:13:05.833
You guys come by sea?

634
01:13:07.833 --> 01:13:09.083
You flying solo?

635
01:13:14.416 --> 01:13:17.000
My pigs are starting
to vibe with you.

636
01:13:17.916 --> 01:13:19.166
You hungry?

637
01:13:21.250 --> 01:13:22.666
Leave your weapons outside

638
01:13:22.916 --> 01:13:25.250
and get some of that
Zeus-style hospitality.

639
01:13:26.750 --> 01:13:29.500
Grab a pig. slaughter
it for dinner.

640
01:13:53.750 --> 01:13:56.250
I don't know who you are.
but you're no peasant.

641
01:13:56.500 --> 01:13:57.500
Let it be.

642
01:14:01.166 --> 01:14:02.750
This stew smells fire.

643
01:14:06.083 --> 01:14:07.916
It'll be enough for both of us.

644
01:14:08.833 --> 01:14:11.083
Who said it was just us two?

645
01:14:12.166 --> 01:14:13.166
Who else is around?

646
01:14:13.583 --> 01:14:14.833
That's the
million-dollar question.

647
01:14:27.833 --> 01:14:28.916
You claim you're alone.

648
01:14:29.833 --> 01:14:31.416
but nobody rolls up here alone.

649
01:14:32.416 --> 01:14:33.416
Is that right?

650
01:14:33.916 --> 01:14:36.083
You can only reach
this place by sea.

651
01:14:37.333 --> 01:14:39.083
Where's your crew?

652
01:14:40.000 --> 01:14:41.333
I'm trying to find them.

653
01:14:42.166 --> 01:14:43.416
Anyone else been here?

654
01:14:46.833 --> 01:14:49.333
There's so much food.
- You doubting me?

655
01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:51.000
You?

656
01:14:52.833 --> 01:14:56.500
A clearly starving traveler
who won't touch the food.

657
01:14:57.333 --> 01:14:59.083
who claims he's a sailor

658
01:14:59.250 --> 01:15:01.333
but rocks the armor
of a legit warrior.

659
01:15:01.750 --> 01:15:03.583
and who disrespects
the laws of Zeus.

660
01:15:04.083 --> 01:15:06.750
packing a dagger
where he's invited.

661
01:15:06.916 --> 01:15:08.166
You've got a sharp eye.

662
01:15:08.666 --> 01:15:10.416
Sharpened by the gods.

663
01:15:10.833 --> 01:15:12.666
They feeding you secrets?

664
01:15:12.916 --> 01:15:14.083
Truths.

665
01:15:15.166 --> 01:15:16.500
sometimes.

666
01:15:16.666 --> 01:15:18.666
Do they know where my guys are?

667
01:15:19.666 --> 01:15:21.833
Your crew?
- Exactly.

668
01:15:22.500 --> 01:15:23.583
They'd know.

669
01:15:24.000 --> 01:15:25.000
You gonna tell me?

670
01:15:25.666 --> 01:15:26.666
Maybe.

671
01:15:28.583 --> 01:15:30.583
If you hand over that dagger.

672
01:15:38.500 --> 01:15:41.416
But why would I help a liar who
didn't respect my hospitality?

673
01:15:52.250 --> 01:15:54.916
Your guys showed up
and now they're gone.

674
01:16:01.250 --> 01:16:02.416
They dipped?

675
01:16:06.750 --> 01:16:08.416
Leaving their rings behind?

676
01:16:15.916 --> 01:16:16.916
Bad move.

677
01:16:18.833 --> 01:16:21.166
No!
- What's with this bird of yours?

678
01:16:21.416 --> 01:16:24.250
Drop the dagger or I'll
choke her out to get answers.

679
01:16:24.583 --> 01:16:26.833
Leave her alone.
- She family?

680
01:16:28.916 --> 01:16:29.916
Your mom?

681
01:16:32.166 --> 01:16:33.166
Your sister.

682
01:16:36.916 --> 01:16:39.250
You turned her into this.
and my crew into pigs.

683
01:16:39.500 --> 01:16:42.333
I didn't turn your crew
into anything. look at them!

684
01:16:42.666 --> 01:16:44.416
This is what they
actually are. peep it!

685
01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:47.333
These gross

686
01:16:47.500 --> 01:16:49.833
and animal instincts you
love so much in battle!

687
01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:52.500
They were out raping and pillaging
everywhere because of you.

688
01:16:52.916 --> 01:16:56.583
You really think they were forced
to do it just to listen to you?

689
01:16:56.916 --> 01:17:01.500
A leader confuses his men's
savagery for discipline.

690
01:17:01.750 --> 01:17:03.750
You don't seem that clueless.

691
01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:05.666
but you still sent them here.

692
01:17:05.833 --> 01:17:07.250
where I live by myself.

693
01:17:07.416 --> 01:17:09.166
A pack of trash soldiers

694
01:17:09.333 --> 01:17:11.833
with empty bellies
and hot blood!

695
01:17:13.500 --> 01:17:15.416
Did you think they'd respect me

696
01:17:15.583 --> 01:17:16.750
in my own house?

697
01:17:17.083 --> 01:17:19.666
Look at them. get
to know your crew!

698
01:17:21.500 --> 01:17:22.750
Did they hurt you?

699
01:17:23.166 --> 01:17:24.416
They would have.

700
01:17:25.166 --> 01:17:26.833
They just want to go home.

701
01:17:30.500 --> 01:17:31.583
Let 'em go home.

702
01:17:58.250 --> 01:17:59.416
Turn back.

703
01:18:00.666 --> 01:18:01.916
Turn back.

704
01:18:04.583 --> 01:18:06.750
Put your disguise back on.

705
01:18:11.000 --> 01:18:12.166
Turn back.

706
01:18:12.666 --> 01:18:14.833
Put your disguise back on.

707
01:18:32.583 --> 01:18:33.583
Odysseus.

708
01:18:34.250 --> 01:18:37.333
We're heading back on board.
stocking up on supplies.

709
01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:39.083
Leave the meat.

710
01:18:39.500 --> 01:18:41.666
Don't let this witch live.

711
01:18:42.333 --> 01:18:45.333
Who gave her those
powers? Your gods.

712
01:18:45.750 --> 01:18:47.166
Get water.

713
01:18:47.333 --> 01:18:49.166
We're setting sail at dawn.

714
01:18:54.750 --> 01:18:56.333
Why are you leaving
her like that?

715
01:18:56.916 --> 01:18:58.833
We understand each
other better this way.

716
01:19:00.166 --> 01:19:02.166
Sorry if we offended you.

717
01:19:03.500 --> 01:19:05.416
Help us get home.

718
01:19:05.750 --> 01:19:07.583
to find the trade routes.

719
01:19:07.750 --> 01:19:09.166
You're way too lost.

720
01:19:09.583 --> 01:19:11.000
What's that supposed to mean?

721
01:19:12.250 --> 01:19:12.477
The blind Tiresias knew...

722
01:19:12.501 --> 01:19:15.000
Only the blind
Tiresias knows the way.

723
01:19:15.250 --> 01:19:17.583
Tiresias? In the underworld.

724
01:19:18.083 --> 01:19:18.500
Nobody sails to hell

725
01:19:18.833 --> 01:19:21.083
and makes it back.

726
01:19:21.333 --> 01:19:22.333
You will.

727
01:19:23.833 --> 01:19:25.750
Sail north. toward the twilight.

728
01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:35.333
Then head into the lands
where the river of fire

729
01:19:35.500 --> 01:19:37.083
meets the river of ice.

730
01:20:28.750 --> 01:20:30.333
Dig a pit there.

731
01:20:33.666 --> 01:20:35.500
pour in the blood
of a sacrifice.

732
01:20:55.416 --> 01:20:56.583
call up the dead

733
01:20:57.750 --> 01:20:59.416
and figure out how to get home.

734
01:21:01.500 --> 01:21:02.583
Just you.

735
01:21:03.750 --> 01:21:05.083
not your men.

736
01:21:05.666 --> 01:21:07.000
You cursing them?

737
01:21:07.333 --> 01:21:08.500
Not a curse.

738
01:21:09.583 --> 01:21:10.750
just the facts.

739
01:21:11.666 --> 01:21:14.333
Your men don't want
you to defy the gods.

740
01:21:15.750 --> 01:21:18.000
but the gods say only
you are making it back.

741
01:21:19.166 --> 01:21:20.833
Then I'll defy the gods.

742
01:22:00.666 --> 01:22:01.833
Sinon.

743
01:22:02.333 --> 01:22:03.500
This is Odysseus.

744
01:22:07.916 --> 01:22:08.916
Sinon.

745
01:22:10.083 --> 01:22:11.083
this is Odysseus.

746
01:22:13.666 --> 01:22:15.250
Let him drink. Odysseus.

747
01:22:16.166 --> 01:22:17.916
and you'll hear his story.

748
01:22:31.833 --> 01:22:32.916
Odysseus?

749
01:22:34.666 --> 01:22:36.583
You lied to everyone.

750
01:22:39.833 --> 01:22:41.750
Did you have to lie to me too?

751
01:22:42.750 --> 01:22:44.166
You needed to believe.

752
01:22:46.250 --> 01:22:48.083
Why'd you volunteer?

753
01:22:48.416 --> 01:22:49.833
You don't remember?

754
01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:52.750
I begged to take
Antinous's spot.

755
01:22:53.166 --> 01:22:54.583
when they snatched him up.

756
01:22:55.083 --> 01:22:58.250
He'd paid your family
to take his place.

757
01:22:58.750 --> 01:23:00.750
If the Trojans
don't let me live.

758
01:23:03.166 --> 01:23:04.500
if I don't make it back.

759
01:23:05.000 --> 01:23:06.666
get this to my pops.

760
01:23:07.833 --> 01:23:09.750
Tell him everything I did.

761
01:23:12.416 --> 01:23:13.500
Odysseus?

762
01:23:15.583 --> 01:23:17.750
Feel free to hype it up a bit.

763
01:23:21.250 --> 01:23:23.416
Didn't you trust me
with the real deal?

764
01:23:25.333 --> 01:23:27.333
I was down to die for you!

765
01:23:27.583 --> 01:23:30.750
When you're dying. you speak the
truth. You had to believe it.

766
01:23:31.250 --> 01:23:33.333
I died because you lied.

767
01:23:34.083 --> 01:23:36.250
I know. I was right
there with you.

768
01:23:36.750 --> 01:23:39.666
I heard you gasping out that
lie with your last breath

769
01:23:39.833 --> 01:23:41.916
that won us the whole war.

770
01:23:42.166 --> 01:23:44.333
I was so close I
could feel your blood.

771
01:23:44.500 --> 01:23:46.750
How does it help me

772
01:23:47.916 --> 01:23:52.000
to find out you only got in
that horse thanks to the dead?

773
01:23:53.166 --> 01:23:54.250
Which dead ones?

774
01:23:54.666 --> 01:23:58.250
Lots of vets from your battles
are wandering around here.

775
01:24:00.333 --> 01:24:03.333
The dead hang out
to mourn the living

776
01:24:03.583 --> 01:24:05.666
and welcome the new guys.

777
01:24:06.416 --> 01:24:08.250
My dad's ghost found me.

778
01:24:09.083 --> 01:24:12.083
To give you some peace?
- Ghosts don't give peace.

779
01:24:12.833 --> 01:24:16.083
They ask about the living
who did them wrong.

780
01:24:17.000 --> 01:24:19.500
My pops died broke.

781
01:24:19.916 --> 01:24:21.000
all alone.

782
01:24:21.250 --> 01:24:24.666
begging for scraps from
creeps like Antinous.

783
01:24:24.916 --> 01:24:26.583
Did Antinous screw you over?

784
01:24:27.250 --> 01:24:29.416
And he's probably doing
the same thing to you.

785
01:24:29.583 --> 01:24:32.916
How so?
- Who's looking out for your wife and kid?

786
01:24:33.500 --> 01:24:35.583
My wife's not my problem.

787
01:24:36.750 --> 01:24:39.333
Ask Agamemnon about how
his homecoming went.

788
01:24:40.083 --> 01:24:41.500
Is Agamemnon around?

789
01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:47.250
You gave me a proper
burial in Troy.

790
01:24:47.416 --> 01:24:48.416
thanks for that.

791
01:24:49.333 --> 01:24:51.083
but you left others behind.

792
01:24:51.750 --> 01:24:53.666
I did what I could.

793
01:24:54.333 --> 01:24:55.750
When you get back.

794
01:24:56.500 --> 01:24:57.500
grab a ship.

795
01:24:57.833 --> 01:25:00.750
sail west into the unknown
until you hit land.

796
01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:03.000
And then offer a sacrifice

797
01:25:03.416 --> 01:25:05.250
and show your crew some respect.

798
01:25:07.250 --> 01:25:08.833
Still got the lot?

799
01:25:12.416 --> 01:25:13.416
Obviously.

800
01:25:14.083 --> 01:25:15.083
If you make it back.

801
01:25:15.333 --> 01:25:17.333
make Antinous pay ten times
over for being such a jerk.

802
01:25:17.750 --> 01:25:18.833
Count on it.

803
01:25:30.250 --> 01:25:31.416
My king.

804
01:25:43.166 --> 01:25:44.416
Odysseus.

805
01:25:45.166 --> 01:25:46.500
What are you doing here?

806
01:25:47.166 --> 01:25:49.500
You were supposed to be
heading home a winner.

807
01:25:49.750 --> 01:25:50.916
You. Odysseus.

808
01:25:51.500 --> 01:25:55.750
my best general. shouldn't
get trapped like me.

809
01:25:56.416 --> 01:25:58.833
Are you just as lost as us?

810
01:26:00.083 --> 01:26:02.583
My bad luck was that I
actually made it home.

811
01:26:03.916 --> 01:26:06.000
that my gorgeous
wife greeted me.

812
01:26:11.833 --> 01:26:12.833
got me cleaned up.

813
01:26:15.500 --> 01:26:16.500
scented.

814
01:26:19.083 --> 01:26:20.250
softened up.

815
01:26:21.500 --> 01:26:23.500
only to learn a brutal lesson:

816
01:26:24.416 --> 01:26:26.750
that I'd poisoned her heart.

817
01:26:29.500 --> 01:26:31.333
that she was into someone else.

818
01:26:37.500 --> 01:26:41.000
Her and her side piece had been
plotting to ice me for years.

819
01:26:41.833 --> 01:26:42.833
Odysseus?

820
01:26:45.583 --> 01:26:47.000
My son Orestes.

821
01:26:47.500 --> 01:26:48.833
did he get revenge for me?

822
01:26:49.083 --> 01:26:50.250
How would I know?

823
01:26:51.500 --> 01:26:53.083
I'm still trying to
find my way home.

824
01:26:54.333 --> 01:26:56.083
Don't trip like I did.

825
01:26:57.000 --> 01:27:00.416
don't just waltz through the front
door expecting cheers and medals.

826
01:27:00.833 --> 01:27:02.166
Roll up on the low.

827
01:27:02.750 --> 01:27:03.833
take your time.

828
01:27:04.750 --> 01:27:05.833
scope it out.

829
01:27:12.833 --> 01:27:14.083
You get me?

830
01:27:15.833 --> 01:27:18.916
I know the plan.
- Only partially.

831
01:27:19.083 --> 01:27:21.500
This prophecy isn't for them.

832
01:27:22.750 --> 01:27:23.833
Get back on the boat.

833
01:27:25.833 --> 01:27:26.916
Head southwest.

834
01:27:27.083 --> 01:27:28.916
give those sirens a wide berth.

835
01:27:29.750 --> 01:27:32.916
Their vibe will drag your crew
down and everyone's toast.

836
01:27:33.166 --> 01:27:34.583
I'll handle that.

837
01:27:35.166 --> 01:27:37.333
I'll plug their ears with wax.

838
01:27:37.500 --> 01:27:38.500
After the sirens.

839
01:27:38.750 --> 01:27:42.333
you've got a choice between the
whirlpool Charybdis and the beast Scylla.

840
01:27:42.750 --> 01:27:45.166
The whirlpool kills everyone.

841
01:27:45.333 --> 01:27:47.416
the cliff monster
only takes six.

842
01:27:47.666 --> 01:27:51.583
But if you're too stubborn to
lose a few. everyone's gonna die.

843
01:27:52.916 --> 01:27:53.916
I'll make the call.

844
01:27:54.000 --> 01:27:56.666
Eventually. when they're
starving and turning on you.

845
01:27:56.833 --> 01:28:00.583
they'll want to hit the shore
where the sun god keeps his cattle.

846
01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:03.083
and they're gonna
slaughter Apollo's herd.

847
01:28:03.916 --> 01:28:05.500
Zeus is gonna wipe
them out as payback.

848
01:28:05.750 --> 01:28:06.750
See?

849
01:28:07.916 --> 01:28:09.166
I'll keep them in line.

850
01:28:09.250 --> 01:28:12.500
Why do you care more about these
guys than the ones already gone?

851
01:28:12.583 --> 01:28:14.500
I can still save
them from the gods.

852
01:28:15.750 --> 01:28:17.583
But not from themselves.

853
01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:21.000
What's this?

854
01:28:21.166 --> 01:28:22.500
Your crew who didn't get buried.

855
01:28:26.000 --> 01:28:28.416
They want you to
feel their shame.

856
01:28:30.166 --> 01:28:31.333
Hurry!

857
01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:16.083
Is this our fate?

858
01:29:19.000 --> 01:29:20.500
Is this our destiny?

859
01:29:40.583 --> 01:29:42.666
We made it out of Hell.

860
01:29:43.916 --> 01:29:46.166
leaving so many of
our boys behind.

861
01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:49.000
I've gotta save the rest.

862
01:29:49.500 --> 01:29:51.166
What happened to them?

863
01:29:51.416 --> 01:29:52.666
Did they just leave me here?

864
01:29:53.166 --> 01:29:54.333
Are they coming back?

865
01:29:56.583 --> 01:29:57.750
Did you attack them?

866
01:29:59.750 --> 01:30:01.250
Did you attack them?

867
01:30:01.666 --> 01:30:02.666
Eat.

868
01:30:02.833 --> 01:30:05.000
You told me to kill
the lotus vibe.

869
01:30:05.166 --> 01:30:08.500
Just for tonight. so
you can catch some Z's.

870
01:30:11.833 --> 01:30:15.250
And tomorrow. when you're good.
it'll all come back to you.

871
01:30:18.000 --> 01:30:19.916
You'll remember your crew.

872
01:30:20.500 --> 01:30:21.500
your family.

873
01:30:24.500 --> 01:30:25.500
A wife?

874
01:30:27.416 --> 01:30:28.916
I've got a wife?

875
01:30:34.250 --> 01:30:36.083
Don't trip. Melantho!

876
01:30:36.416 --> 01:30:37.833
No stranger's getting in here.

877
01:30:38.000 --> 01:30:39.250
Even with this wall between us.

878
01:30:39.416 --> 01:30:42.250
after three years I'm not really
a stranger to you anymore.

879
01:30:42.833 --> 01:30:46.166
You trying to wife
me up or ruin my rep?

880
01:30:46.333 --> 01:30:47.500
Melantho's on the down-low.

881
01:30:48.250 --> 01:30:51.750
That's exactly why I'm here -
because I'm looking out for your rep.

882
01:30:53.083 --> 01:30:54.666
We all see you grinding.

883
01:30:54.916 --> 01:30:57.416
I'm making progress.
slow but steady.

884
01:30:58.916 --> 01:31:01.500
But every night you
undo all your work.

885
01:31:07.416 --> 01:31:08.416
Leave us.

886
01:31:10.333 --> 01:31:14.166
You can't expect her to stay
loyal to a boss she doesn't know.

887
01:31:14.333 --> 01:31:16.166
I thought she was down for me.

888
01:31:16.416 --> 01:31:19.083
She will be. once you marry me.

889
01:31:20.166 --> 01:31:21.166
The help

890
01:31:21.416 --> 01:31:23.916
needs to save their
loyalty for what's coming.

891
01:31:24.500 --> 01:31:26.250
and this house is looking
for a new head of the table.

892
01:31:26.666 --> 01:31:29.250
just like Ithaca is
looking for a king.

893
01:31:31.583 --> 01:31:33.416
The king of Ithaca
is coming back.

894
01:31:33.916 --> 01:31:35.250
Doubt it.

895
01:31:36.833 --> 01:31:39.750
Did you know that when I was a
kid I wanted to tag along to Troy?

896
01:31:41.000 --> 01:31:42.666
He didn't mention it to me.

897
01:31:44.000 --> 01:31:45.166
Odysseus said no.

898
01:31:45.583 --> 01:31:49.250
He knew Ithaca needed a future
without him in the picture.

899
01:31:56.000 --> 01:31:58.500
And you saw me as
part of that future.

900
01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:06.083
I won't tell the
other suitors about

901
01:32:07.166 --> 01:32:08.666
what you're pulling.

902
01:32:10.833 --> 01:32:12.666
Get back to work.

903
01:32:14.500 --> 01:32:16.333
Time to let him go.

904
01:32:25.750 --> 01:32:28.916
Why even bother marrying a woman
who's stuck on someone else?

905
01:32:31.583 --> 01:32:34.166
Your loyalty to Odysseus

906
01:32:34.416 --> 01:32:36.750
is honestly one of
your best traits.

907
01:32:39.916 --> 01:32:41.250
I'm feeling you.

908
01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:45.333
I want you to pick me and
just dead this whole thing.

909
01:32:46.833 --> 01:32:49.666
Don't front like
you aren't tired

910
01:32:50.333 --> 01:32:53.250
of all the waiting
and the guessing.

911
01:32:55.250 --> 01:32:58.166
You've been holding it down

912
01:32:59.166 --> 01:33:01.416
year after year.

913
01:33:01.666 --> 01:33:03.083
after year.

914
01:33:05.916 --> 01:33:07.916
Time to put yourself first.

915
01:33:09.500 --> 01:33:11.083
and get back to
living your life.

916
01:33:16.750 --> 01:33:18.583
That's what Odysseus would want.

917
01:33:25.583 --> 01:33:27.000
I'll look out for you.

918
01:33:32.000 --> 01:33:33.166
My queen.

919
01:33:36.416 --> 01:33:37.666
And my son?

920
01:33:39.250 --> 01:33:41.833
The throne is his.
He's the heir.

921
01:33:44.916 --> 01:33:47.000
Unless we have a kid of our own.

922
01:33:57.250 --> 01:33:58.500
Where's Telemachus?

923
01:34:00.166 --> 01:34:01.583
Out in the country.

924
01:34:01.750 --> 01:34:03.500
visiting his grandpops.

925
01:34:11.166 --> 01:34:12.500
She's capping.

926
01:34:12.666 --> 01:34:14.333
he sailed.

927
01:34:28.083 --> 01:34:29.750
He's out looking for his dad.

928
01:34:30.666 --> 01:34:31.333
Where?

929
01:34:31.583 --> 01:34:32.666
Sparta.

930
01:34:32.833 --> 01:34:34.250
to see Menelaus.

931
01:34:35.250 --> 01:34:36.833
Do we really have to go there?

932
01:34:40.000 --> 01:34:43.166
You're always way too loud.
Melanthius. especially for a cowherd!

933
01:34:44.166 --> 01:34:45.416
He was creeping on us!

934
01:34:48.833 --> 01:34:50.083
I was just looking for Argos.

935
01:34:51.583 --> 01:34:53.833
He stays where he is.
Head back to the farm.

936
01:34:54.250 --> 01:34:56.583
We'll send Melanthius
to go grab your pigs.

937
01:34:57.166 --> 01:34:59.250
Nobody asked for
you here. old man.

938
01:34:59.416 --> 01:35:01.666
I only listen to my mistress.

939
01:35:03.583 --> 01:35:05.000
Does she even know who you are?

940
01:35:06.333 --> 01:35:07.333
Beat it!

941
01:35:07.916 --> 01:35:11.083
Telemachus is definitely gonna
roll through that temple in Pylos.

942
01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:13.750
Catch him there with your crew.

943
01:35:14.000 --> 01:35:15.666
And leave you here to
flirt with the queen?

944
01:35:16.083 --> 01:35:17.166
No way.

945
01:35:18.000 --> 01:35:19.750
He needs to be taken
out on the way.

946
01:35:20.000 --> 01:35:21.500
Irus has a scheme.

947
01:35:25.500 --> 01:35:29.083
I want him and his boys dead in
a ditch with their throats slit.

948
01:35:29.333 --> 01:35:34.166
Telemachus and his crew will be
ready for bandits on the road.

949
01:35:34.916 --> 01:35:38.166
but if those bandits are
hiding in the temple...

950
01:35:39.583 --> 01:35:42.083
Bring me a piece
of him for proof.

951
01:35:43.166 --> 01:35:44.166
His nose.

952
01:35:44.833 --> 01:35:47.000
You'd only know him by his nose?

953
01:35:49.916 --> 01:35:51.416
And his ears too.

954
01:35:56.416 --> 01:35:57.583
Who trained you?

955
01:35:58.000 --> 01:35:59.416
My dad's swineherd.

956
01:35:59.583 --> 01:36:02.166
His swineherd? His
day-one servant.

957
01:36:02.916 --> 01:36:05.666
Odysseus left his
best guy behind?

958
01:36:05.833 --> 01:36:07.833
He was always the smart one.

959
01:36:08.166 --> 01:36:10.583
Agamemnon only took
advice from him.

960
01:36:11.250 --> 01:36:12.750
Should've listened a bit more.

961
01:36:13.250 --> 01:36:14.583
What happened to your brother?

962
01:36:14.833 --> 01:36:15.916
His wife played him.

963
01:36:16.416 --> 01:36:17.416
she offed him.

964
01:36:17.833 --> 01:36:18.833
What'd he do?

965
01:36:19.000 --> 01:36:21.000
His son Orestes
handled them both.

966
01:36:21.833 --> 01:36:23.166
He killed his own mom?

967
01:36:24.333 --> 01:36:25.416
He was getting
payback for his pops.

968
01:36:26.583 --> 01:36:27.833
but don't trip.

969
01:36:28.000 --> 01:36:30.500
your mom is nothing
like Clytemnestra.

970
01:36:30.666 --> 01:36:31.666
Maybe.

971
01:36:32.083 --> 01:36:35.333
but the suitors talked the elders
into forcing her to remarry.

972
01:36:35.916 --> 01:36:38.166
It's not a good look for
the throne to be empty.

973
01:36:38.333 --> 01:36:40.500
You know the word
on the Sea People.

974
01:36:41.083 --> 01:36:44.416
Did they hit you?
- Nah. but trouble's brewing.

975
01:36:44.750 --> 01:36:45.916
Sparta's ready.

976
01:36:46.333 --> 01:36:47.666
And Ithaca?

977
01:36:47.916 --> 01:36:50.250
She's gotta be able to
pull an army together.

978
01:36:50.416 --> 01:36:51.750
The throne needs a boss.

979
01:36:51.916 --> 01:36:54.666
So that's where the
real fight is. kid.

980
01:36:55.250 --> 01:36:56.666
You bailed on your problems

981
01:36:57.916 --> 01:37:01.000
and left your mom to
deal with those suitors.

982
01:37:01.833 --> 01:37:03.583
Should I hire some muscle?

983
01:37:03.833 --> 01:37:05.916
Go home and wipe them out?

984
01:37:06.166 --> 01:37:08.333
Kill a bunch of rich.
powerful guests?

985
01:37:09.083 --> 01:37:10.583
You'll get exiled.

986
01:37:11.250 --> 01:37:12.333
So what am I supposed to do?

987
01:37:12.583 --> 01:37:15.666
Take them out without
breaking Zeus's law.

988
01:37:17.583 --> 01:37:19.166
I gotta take the throne

989
01:37:20.666 --> 01:37:22.833
and figure out if
Odysseus is even alive.

990
01:37:23.000 --> 01:37:26.416
This isn't about some dad
you never even really knew.

991
01:37:27.166 --> 01:37:28.583
You need to step
up like a leader.

992
01:37:29.166 --> 01:37:30.666
no matter where Odysseus is.

993
01:37:44.833 --> 01:37:46.166
You gotta remember.

994
01:37:46.583 --> 01:37:47.666
Nah.

995
01:37:48.583 --> 01:37:51.916
I'm cool without the truth.
I'm vibing here with you.

996
01:37:53.750 --> 01:37:57.666
Then why are you collecting
scraps to build a raft?

997
01:38:00.416 --> 01:38:02.250
Remember your crew.

998
01:38:03.583 --> 01:38:04.583
your mission.

999
01:38:09.166 --> 01:38:11.500
I've heard about
the sirens' song.

1000
01:38:21.416 --> 01:38:23.750
Plug their ears with wax.

1001
01:38:24.250 --> 01:38:26.166
Not mine. Tie me to the mast.

1002
01:38:26.333 --> 01:38:28.666
Why?
- To hear the sirens.

1003
01:38:30.833 --> 01:38:33.583
Bad move. Nobody's ever
walked away from that.

1004
01:38:33.750 --> 01:38:36.000
I'll be the first.

1005
01:38:37.083 --> 01:38:38.583
Even if I'm begging you.

1006
01:38:38.750 --> 01:38:41.166
don't let me go
until we're clear.

1007
01:38:42.583 --> 01:38:44.250
Check their ears.

1008
01:38:44.666 --> 01:38:47.750
Double food for the first
one who says. "I hear it!"

1009
01:39:47.416 --> 01:39:49.083
What was that song about?

1010
01:39:50.166 --> 01:39:52.083
Everything a guy could want.

1011
01:39:52.833 --> 01:39:53.833
and then

1012
01:39:54.166 --> 01:39:56.833
everything we wish we'd never
wanted in the first place.

1013
01:40:13.583 --> 01:40:16.500
It was like that sweet itch
you can't stop scratching.

1014
01:40:17.583 --> 01:40:20.666
before you realize it's deep under
your skin. totally out of reach.

1015
01:40:22.416 --> 01:40:25.333
Then the itch just
drives you crazy.

1016
01:40:29.000 --> 01:40:31.250
It said the things
we want the most

1017
01:40:32.916 --> 01:40:34.916
are the most off-limits.

1018
01:40:38.250 --> 01:40:40.083
and the most off-limits stuff

1019
01:40:41.333 --> 01:40:42.916
is what we already had

1020
01:40:43.750 --> 01:40:45.000
and lost.

1021
01:40:52.833 --> 01:40:55.250
It was the song of all
the promises I broke.

1022
01:41:00.416 --> 01:41:03.083
It told me I don't
really wanna go home.

1023
01:41:05.583 --> 01:41:06.750
It's bubbling up!

1024
01:41:07.500 --> 01:41:08.500
Straight ahead!

1025
01:41:11.416 --> 01:41:12.500
Charybdis.

1026
01:41:13.583 --> 01:41:14.916
that crazy whirlpool.

1027
01:41:17.500 --> 01:41:18.500
Get the sails up!

1028
01:41:19.166 --> 01:41:20.250
Hurry!

1029
01:41:20.416 --> 01:41:22.083
Pull the anchor!

1030
01:41:22.500 --> 01:41:23.666
Into the open sea?

1031
01:41:23.916 --> 01:41:25.000
It's already sucking us in.

1032
01:41:28.500 --> 01:41:30.166
Go north!

1033
01:41:31.166 --> 01:41:33.250
Through the strait?
- It's way too tight.

1034
01:41:33.750 --> 01:41:35.083
Hit the whirlpool.

1035
01:41:35.250 --> 01:41:39.083
ride the edge to get some speed
and pop out the other side.

1036
01:41:39.250 --> 01:41:40.750
Stay strong. we'll make it.

1037
01:41:47.916 --> 01:41:50.250
We're going through
the strait. The strait!

1038
01:41:54.083 --> 01:41:55.083
Oars in!

1039
01:41:55.750 --> 01:41:56.750
Starboard side.

1040
01:41:57.000 --> 01:41:58.333
ready to stop!

1041
01:42:05.000 --> 01:42:06.000
Wait for my signal!

1042
01:42:13.750 --> 01:42:15.333
Oars out!

1043
01:43:03.166 --> 01:43:04.416
We made it through!

1044
01:43:04.833 --> 01:43:05.833
We actually did it!

1045
01:43:06.833 --> 01:43:07.833
We did it.

1046
01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:09.000
Thank the gods.

1047
01:43:20.166 --> 01:43:21.416
Stay on course!

1048
01:43:29.416 --> 01:43:30.416
Hold that line!

1049
01:43:58.166 --> 01:43:59.250
You knew

1050
01:43:59.833 --> 01:44:00.833
and didn't say a word!

1051
01:44:01.500 --> 01:44:03.916
You would've said no
to going through here.

1052
01:44:04.250 --> 01:44:07.166
And these guys would
still be breathing!

1053
01:44:07.333 --> 01:44:08.666
We all would've been toast!

1054
01:44:08.916 --> 01:44:10.416
You didn't have the right!

1055
01:44:10.583 --> 01:44:13.666
That was totally my call
and my responsibility!

1056
01:44:13.833 --> 01:44:16.833
That whirlpool would've
swallowed every single one of us.

1057
01:44:17.000 --> 01:44:19.250
At least we made it out.
- Not all of us!

1058
01:44:24.000 --> 01:44:25.666
What else did Tiresias say?

1059
01:44:38.000 --> 01:44:39.500
I'm landing there!

1060
01:44:42.083 --> 01:44:45.250
We can't. this is
the Sun God's turf!

1061
01:44:45.500 --> 01:44:47.083
We need to fix the ship!

1062
01:44:48.250 --> 01:44:51.250
The boys are cooked. we
lost six dudes already!

1063
01:44:51.916 --> 01:44:54.583
We're going on land
to crash for a bit.

1064
01:44:54.750 --> 01:44:56.083
You're all gonna die!

1065
01:44:59.416 --> 01:45:01.166
What was it Tiresias told me?

1066
01:45:02.416 --> 01:45:04.000
That you're all gonna die.

1067
01:45:04.583 --> 01:45:05.666
if you slaughter

1068
01:45:06.833 --> 01:45:09.916
the Sun God's cattle
that live on this island.

1069
01:45:10.166 --> 01:45:11.166
You're all gonna die.

1070
01:45:15.666 --> 01:45:16.833
In that case.

1071
01:45:17.666 --> 01:45:20.833
we land. but we only
eat our own stash.

1072
01:45:21.000 --> 01:45:22.333
We grab some fruit.

1073
01:45:22.500 --> 01:45:24.750
get some water. and that's it!

1074
01:45:25.416 --> 01:45:26.833
Swear it.

1075
01:45:27.416 --> 01:45:28.583
All of you. swear it.

1076
01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:44.083
See that?

1077
01:45:44.833 --> 01:45:46.250
The wind is pushing
us right there!

1078
01:45:47.416 --> 01:45:49.666
We rest. fix up the ship.

1079
01:45:50.416 --> 01:45:52.500
and bail as soon as
the breeze shifts.

1080
01:45:53.333 --> 01:45:54.666
Grab that rope!

1081
01:46:05.083 --> 01:46:06.916
Did your guys stick
to their word?

1082
01:46:07.833 --> 01:46:08.833
Yeah.

1083
01:46:09.666 --> 01:46:10.916
For a while.

1084
01:46:12.416 --> 01:46:13.833
But the wind never changed.

1085
01:46:14.000 --> 01:46:18.083
That same breeze that got
us to the shore so easy

1086
01:46:20.250 --> 01:46:21.666
kept us stuck there.

1087
01:46:25.916 --> 01:46:27.916
And we started
running out of food.

1088
01:46:30.666 --> 01:46:31.666
Run!

1089
01:47:31.666 --> 01:47:34.916
Did you really think you could
sneak a meal and fool the Sun God?

1090
01:47:35.083 --> 01:47:36.833
To fool you.

1091
01:47:37.250 --> 01:47:38.666
I'm not the problem.

1092
01:47:38.833 --> 01:47:40.416
I was just trying to
keep you guys alive.

1093
01:47:45.666 --> 01:47:49.500
Tiresias warned you. Circe
and the gods warned you too.

1094
01:47:50.333 --> 01:47:52.750
The gods don't make any sense.

1095
01:47:52.916 --> 01:47:55.166
Who doesn't get
what suffering is?

1096
01:47:55.583 --> 01:47:57.416
Blood. death?

1097
01:47:57.916 --> 01:48:01.500
Do you see losing a man as bad luck or
as something you brought on yourself?

1098
01:48:01.666 --> 01:48:04.833
I see it as me failing them.

1099
01:48:05.083 --> 01:48:07.666
What if they died
because they failed?

1100
01:48:07.916 --> 01:48:09.500
I'm their leader.

1101
01:48:10.666 --> 01:48:12.166
I brought them here.

1102
01:48:12.416 --> 01:48:14.000
And who brought you?

1103
01:48:15.083 --> 01:48:19.333
Why do you think you're bigger than
the gods and take all that on yourself?

1104
01:48:19.583 --> 01:48:21.416
Why don't you want to go back?

1105
01:48:21.583 --> 01:48:23.083
What were you even hoping for?

1106
01:48:24.750 --> 01:48:26.750
They had zero food left.

1107
01:48:27.333 --> 01:48:28.333
Have some mercy!

1108
01:48:28.500 --> 01:48:31.500
Because I was merciful.
we're on this piece of junk!

1109
01:48:31.666 --> 01:48:34.333
I warned you!
- That's facts.

1110
01:48:35.000 --> 01:48:38.416
And we decided to drown
rather than starve to death.

1111
01:48:44.000 --> 01:48:46.250
This is our shot.

1112
01:48:46.416 --> 01:48:48.750
The wind died down!

1113
01:48:52.916 --> 01:48:57.083
This calm was just a trap to
get us into Poseidon's ocean

1114
01:48:58.166 --> 01:49:00.000
under Zeus's watch.

1115
01:49:01.250 --> 01:49:03.166
Steer against the wind!

1116
01:49:19.916 --> 01:49:21.833
Pray to the gods!

1117
01:49:43.416 --> 01:49:45.250
Steer against the wind!

1118
01:49:53.750 --> 01:49:55.416
Steer against the wind!

1119
01:50:09.416 --> 01:50:11.416
Give it up to the gods!

1120
01:50:15.666 --> 01:50:17.583
Pray to Poseidon!

1121
01:50:24.750 --> 01:50:26.916
Beg for a break!

1122
01:50:54.083 --> 01:50:57.166
My last memory was
Zeus's heavy hand.

1123
01:51:08.666 --> 01:51:10.000
Eurylochus!

1124
01:51:39.750 --> 01:51:41.083
I don't know what
happened to them.

1125
01:51:41.333 --> 01:51:42.500
You know.

1126
01:51:44.416 --> 01:51:46.250
The fate you called for them.

1127
01:51:46.666 --> 01:51:48.416
I washed up on your
shore all by myself.

1128
01:51:48.583 --> 01:51:50.750
You washed up on my beach

1129
01:51:50.916 --> 01:51:53.666
with a piece of your boat
and none of your crew.

1130
01:51:55.166 --> 01:51:57.583
half-dead. out cold.

1131
01:52:19.000 --> 01:52:21.000
I looked out for
you. the lost guy.

1132
01:52:21.583 --> 01:52:22.750
for days

1133
01:52:23.000 --> 01:52:24.000
and weeks.

1134
01:52:25.166 --> 01:52:27.833
I knew the lotus would
help you wake up easy.

1135
01:52:29.333 --> 01:52:32.166
that you'd have it rougher in
your body than in your head.

1136
01:52:34.500 --> 01:52:35.750
And it worked!

1137
01:52:38.166 --> 01:52:39.916
You were really feeling it.

1138
01:52:41.000 --> 01:52:42.916
you ate it up no problem.

1139
01:52:46.583 --> 01:52:48.250
And while I took care of you.

1140
01:52:49.000 --> 01:52:50.000
Thanks.

1141
01:52:50.166 --> 01:52:52.083
I started catching feelings.

1142
01:52:57.333 --> 01:52:59.416
How long have I been here?

1143
01:53:01.166 --> 01:53:03.833
I told myself I had
to wean you off it.

1144
01:53:04.083 --> 01:53:06.083
that you were strong
enough to remember.

1145
01:53:06.250 --> 01:53:08.333
Talk to me. Calypso.
- You were happy.

1146
01:53:08.500 --> 01:53:09.666
And you were happy too.

1147
01:53:09.833 --> 01:53:12.000
We were vibing for years.

1148
01:53:12.250 --> 01:53:13.250
For years?

1149
01:53:20.416 --> 01:53:21.416
Seven years.

1150
01:53:22.750 --> 01:53:26.333
You made me eat lotus
flowers to keep me locked up.

1151
01:53:26.583 --> 01:53:27.750
I saved your life.

1152
01:53:28.916 --> 01:53:30.083
I healed your body.

1153
01:53:30.250 --> 01:53:33.166
but I couldn't bring
myself to fix your mind.

1154
01:53:34.750 --> 01:53:35.916
You were happy.

1155
01:53:37.083 --> 01:53:38.333
but your heart

1156
01:53:38.833 --> 01:53:40.333
was always somewhere else.

1157
01:53:41.750 --> 01:53:45.250
and it was only a matter of time
before your head caught up with it.

1158
01:53:46.083 --> 01:53:47.416
How...

1159
01:53:47.583 --> 01:53:49.583
The lotus fogs the brain

1160
01:53:49.750 --> 01:53:53.500
and kills your drive. but it
doesn't change who you really are.

1161
01:53:53.666 --> 01:53:56.500
You weren't ready to go back
without knowing the 'why.'

1162
01:53:57.000 --> 01:53:58.333
Now I am.

1163
01:53:59.833 --> 01:54:01.666
Just like I saw.

1164
01:54:02.500 --> 01:54:03.500
How?

1165
01:54:03.666 --> 01:54:08.250
You kept something gripped tight
in your hand those first few weeks

1166
01:54:09.250 --> 01:54:10.583
and you'd call out.

1167
01:54:11.250 --> 01:54:12.416
Mostly Athena.

1168
01:54:12.666 --> 01:54:15.500
but sometimes you'd
scream out another name.

1169
01:54:30.166 --> 01:54:31.250
Penelope.

1170
01:54:35.833 --> 01:54:37.416
Help me get back.

1171
01:54:38.500 --> 01:54:39.833
That's what I'm doing.

1172
01:54:40.416 --> 01:54:43.166
You're a guy who tries
to run his own fate.

1173
01:54:44.583 --> 01:54:46.333
But you've got zero
power over this one.

1174
01:54:49.500 --> 01:54:51.916
You gotta give in to the storm.

1175
01:54:52.500 --> 01:54:54.416
give in to Poseidon.

1176
01:54:55.583 --> 01:54:57.083
take your punishment.

1177
01:55:00.000 --> 01:55:01.916
Zeus won't let him kill you.

1178
01:55:06.000 --> 01:55:09.166
Stop fighting. let
go. and just live.

1179
01:55:11.833 --> 01:55:13.416
This is a leap into the unknown.

1180
01:55:13.666 --> 01:55:16.250
that you haven't
taken yet. Odysseus.

1181
01:56:09.500 --> 01:56:10.750
Odysseus?

1182
01:56:18.500 --> 01:56:19.583
Where am I?

1183
01:56:21.500 --> 01:56:23.500
Don't you recognize home?

1184
01:57:00.833 --> 01:57:03.083
Zeus blesses you. strangers.

1185
01:57:03.500 --> 01:57:04.500
How many of you?

1186
01:57:05.083 --> 01:57:06.083
Half a dozen.

1187
01:57:06.666 --> 01:57:07.666
Need some food?

1188
01:57:07.833 --> 01:57:09.083
And supplies

1189
01:57:09.666 --> 01:57:10.750
for the road.

1190
01:57:11.166 --> 01:57:13.500
Where you headed? We need pigs.

1191
01:57:13.666 --> 01:57:15.166
We're going to Pylos.

1192
01:57:15.583 --> 01:57:17.083
You guys pilgrims?

1193
01:57:17.666 --> 01:57:19.000
Do we look like pilgrims?

1194
01:57:19.166 --> 01:57:20.750
My eyes aren't great.

1195
01:57:21.416 --> 01:57:24.916
Zeus says I gotta feed you.
but I can't sell these pigs.

1196
01:57:25.250 --> 01:57:27.500
Don't trip. we ain't paying.

1197
01:57:31.666 --> 01:57:33.500
Tell your mom I said hey.

1198
01:57:36.166 --> 01:57:37.583
Tell her I'm sorry

1199
01:57:37.833 --> 01:57:41.333
for Troy and for everything
that went down in my name.

1200
01:57:47.666 --> 01:57:50.000
I'm sorry I don't have
any news on your dad.

1201
01:57:50.250 --> 01:57:51.250
But you did learn something new

1202
01:57:51.333 --> 01:57:53.333
about what kind of
man he actually is.

1203
01:57:54.500 --> 01:57:57.000
Now I'm even more hyped
to see him one day.

1204
01:58:01.916 --> 01:58:03.916
Where are your guard
dogs at. old man?

1205
01:58:08.166 --> 01:58:10.166
I'm burning what's left of 'em.

1206
01:58:14.250 --> 01:58:16.333
Can Zeus fix you up. stranger?

1207
01:58:17.500 --> 01:58:18.916
Did they try to jump you?

1208
01:58:19.416 --> 01:58:21.416
Did those dogs actually
protect your shepherds?

1209
01:58:22.000 --> 01:58:24.000
Nah. we burned his
brothers first.

1210
01:58:26.333 --> 01:58:28.083
What's the deal with Ithaca?

1211
01:58:28.250 --> 01:58:29.250
It's dark times.

1212
01:58:29.500 --> 01:58:32.166
Zeus's laws are totally trashed.

1213
01:58:32.750 --> 01:58:35.750
a kingdom with no king
since my master died.

1214
01:58:35.916 --> 01:58:36.916
Your master?

1215
01:58:37.750 --> 01:58:39.166
Odysseus.

1216
01:58:39.750 --> 01:58:41.666
The big hero from
the Trojan War.

1217
01:58:43.416 --> 01:58:44.916
But Odysseus is still kicking.

1218
01:58:45.083 --> 01:58:47.583
Another bum with some fake hope!

1219
01:58:47.750 --> 01:58:49.166
Chill out!

1220
01:58:53.083 --> 01:58:54.166
Telemachus...

1221
01:58:56.000 --> 01:58:57.000
Telemachus?

1222
01:58:58.083 --> 01:59:00.083
He's in a bad spot.
I can't help him.

1223
01:59:00.250 --> 01:59:03.666
Other people in Ithaca should
be down to help Odysseus's kid.

1224
01:59:03.833 --> 01:59:06.250
The palace is run
by those posers.

1225
01:59:06.666 --> 01:59:09.166
Nobody's loyal to
Odysseus anymore.

1226
01:59:10.250 --> 01:59:11.666
What about the queen?

1227
01:59:12.583 --> 01:59:14.500
The beautiful and
smart Penelope.

1228
01:59:15.083 --> 01:59:17.250
being held hostage
by these scrubs

1229
01:59:17.416 --> 01:59:19.333
and about to be
forced into marriage.

1230
01:59:19.583 --> 01:59:22.083
what's she gonna do? Especially
without her son around?

1231
01:59:22.666 --> 01:59:23.750
Drink.

1232
01:59:27.916 --> 01:59:29.250
What kind of trouble
is Telemachus in?

1233
01:59:30.250 --> 01:59:32.833
He's heading back from Sparta.

1234
01:59:33.500 --> 01:59:37.666
Those guys sent hitmen to take
him out at the temple in Pylos.

1235
01:59:38.666 --> 01:59:40.500
Hook me up with some
food for the trip.

1236
01:59:40.666 --> 01:59:43.333
You're never gonna catch
up to those hitmen.

1237
01:59:43.500 --> 01:59:46.916
If I hit Pylos before Telemachus.
I can give him a heads-up.

1238
01:59:47.083 --> 01:59:48.333
Why are you helping him out?

1239
01:59:49.250 --> 01:59:50.916
Don't get salty about my answer.

1240
01:59:51.666 --> 01:59:54.333
I served with Odysseus in Troy.
- For real?

1241
01:59:55.750 --> 01:59:58.250
He was a demanding
boss. But fair!

1242
01:59:59.666 --> 02:00:02.000
Solid and worth following.

1243
02:00:02.916 --> 02:00:03.916
Did you love him?

1244
02:00:04.916 --> 02:00:06.416
Like my own kid.

1245
02:00:08.416 --> 02:00:09.666
He ain't dead.

1246
02:00:10.833 --> 02:00:12.166
Will he be back?

1247
02:00:12.833 --> 02:00:14.083
Soon.

1248
02:00:14.250 --> 02:00:16.250
To get his get-back.

1249
02:00:18.333 --> 02:00:20.000
The worst kind.

1250
02:00:29.333 --> 02:00:32.166
I'll do the talking. Let's
keep your identity on the low.

1251
02:00:32.416 --> 02:00:34.750
Then we shouldn't
have brought guards.

1252
02:00:35.083 --> 02:00:37.666
They'll be handy if we
run into drama on the way.

1253
02:00:50.583 --> 02:00:52.333
I've got a message. Hold up!

1254
02:00:54.166 --> 02:00:55.250
Eumaeus sent me!

1255
02:00:57.416 --> 02:00:58.583
Bring that beggar to me.

1256
02:01:00.666 --> 02:01:00.892
IvFlix

1257
02:01:00.916 --> 02:01:01.916
lyFlix.

1258
02:01:04.666 --> 02:01:06.426
Watch free HD movies
and series online

1259
02:01:07.833 --> 02:01:10.583
onlyflix. To.

1260
02:01:16.166 --> 02:01:18.500
Your crew stays here.
and your weapons too.

1261
02:01:35.833 --> 02:01:37.750
Zeus welcomes you. strangers.

1262
02:01:38.000 --> 02:01:39.750
You guys been traveling long?

1263
02:01:40.000 --> 02:01:41.250
Not really.

1264
02:01:42.416 --> 02:01:44.583
You looking to
crash here tonight?

1265
02:01:46.333 --> 02:01:48.750
We're here to make a
sacrifice to Athena.

1266
02:01:51.166 --> 02:01:54.083
And we're open to any
hospitality you've got.

1267
02:01:54.250 --> 02:01:56.416
Fine. The beggar stays outside.

1268
02:01:56.666 --> 02:01:58.500
He's got a message for me.

1269
02:01:59.416 --> 02:02:00.916
Did Eumaeus send you?

1270
02:02:01.916 --> 02:02:02.916
Yeah. boss.

1271
02:02:09.083 --> 02:02:10.500
What's the message?

1272
02:02:11.833 --> 02:02:13.083
It's top secret.

1273
02:02:13.416 --> 02:02:14.583
These guys are...

1274
02:02:15.750 --> 02:02:17.000
These guys are priests.

1275
02:02:35.333 --> 02:02:36.833
Beat it. old man.

1276
02:02:38.166 --> 02:02:39.250
Get lost. stranger.

1277
02:02:42.333 --> 02:02:44.750
I let one old guy
slide this week.

1278
02:02:45.083 --> 02:02:47.333
but he was blind.
I ain't letting...

1279
02:03:27.666 --> 02:03:29.250
Not bad for a beggar.

1280
02:03:29.666 --> 02:03:31.166
Nobody starts as a beggar.

1281
02:03:31.583 --> 02:03:34.500
Put this priest robe
over your armor.

1282
02:03:36.583 --> 02:03:39.083
Help me move him.
- We gotta leave him.

1283
02:03:39.916 --> 02:03:41.416
To slip away unnoticed.

1284
02:03:41.833 --> 02:03:44.833
That's not how we respect the dead.
- This is how we stay alive.

1285
02:03:45.000 --> 02:03:46.166
He was my mentor.

1286
02:03:47.000 --> 02:03:49.583
And maybe Athena in disguise.
- It was Mentor.

1287
02:03:50.250 --> 02:03:54.500
Once we're in the clear. we'll head
to the unknown west to honor him.

1288
02:03:55.083 --> 02:03:57.000
Those were the posers' goons.

1289
02:03:57.166 --> 02:03:59.250
More are coming. Let's bounce.

1290
02:03:59.416 --> 02:04:01.536
In the middle of the night?
- Beats staying here.

1291
02:04:01.750 --> 02:04:04.083
Mentor is at the
old Athena temple.

1292
02:04:04.666 --> 02:04:06.666
For now. let's honor
him with a fire.

1293
02:04:16.250 --> 02:04:17.333
Into the fire!

1294
02:04:44.083 --> 02:04:45.916
So. beggar. you knew Mentor?

1295
02:04:46.083 --> 02:04:48.500
Like I said. I
wasn't born a beggar.

1296
02:04:48.833 --> 02:04:51.500
You've got the eyes of a
wise man. eyes like Athena's.

1297
02:04:51.666 --> 02:04:54.916
Don't go looking for gods in
people. you'll just get let down.

1298
02:04:55.083 --> 02:04:57.000
Then tell me who you are.

1299
02:04:58.333 --> 02:04:59.916
My name's Sinon.

1300
02:05:00.250 --> 02:05:03.583
I'm an old soldier who
fought for your dad in Troy.

1301
02:05:04.250 --> 02:05:05.583
You knew my dad?

1302
02:05:05.750 --> 02:05:08.250
I've been on his side forever.

1303
02:05:09.750 --> 02:05:11.166
So he's still alive?

1304
02:05:11.916 --> 02:05:13.083
He's alive.

1305
02:05:14.416 --> 02:05:15.750
But where is he?

1306
02:05:16.000 --> 02:05:17.583
He's super close

1307
02:05:18.000 --> 02:05:20.583
and sent me as a scout to
see what's going on here.

1308
02:05:21.500 --> 02:05:24.500
My mom won't buy it!
- Don't say a word to her.

1309
02:05:25.666 --> 02:05:26.750
Nothing at all?

1310
02:05:27.833 --> 02:05:28.916
Tell her.

1311
02:05:30.000 --> 02:05:32.583
that you've decided she
needs to find a new husband.

1312
02:05:33.916 --> 02:05:36.250
Is he testing her?
Does he not trust her?

1313
02:05:36.416 --> 02:05:37.583
Nah.

1314
02:05:37.916 --> 02:05:40.583
but she's got every
reason to have moved on.

1315
02:05:41.916 --> 02:05:43.833
Are there any loyal people left?

1316
02:05:44.500 --> 02:05:45.583
A few.

1317
02:05:46.416 --> 02:05:49.083
When Odysseus shows his face.
everyone will fall in line.

1318
02:05:50.083 --> 02:05:52.666
You need to get all the
suitors in the palace.

1319
02:05:53.166 --> 02:05:54.833
That's never a problem.

1320
02:05:55.250 --> 02:05:57.166
Did you bring any
gifts from Menelaus?

1321
02:05:57.333 --> 02:05:58.750
Yeah. on my boat.

1322
02:05:59.000 --> 02:06:00.000
Cool.

1323
02:06:00.500 --> 02:06:02.000
Go back as a prince.

1324
02:06:02.166 --> 02:06:03.666
throw a huge party.

1325
02:06:04.000 --> 02:06:05.416
I'll be there.

1326
02:06:06.166 --> 02:06:07.666
What are you gonna do there?

1327
02:06:08.416 --> 02:06:09.500
I'm gonna beg.

1328
02:06:10.000 --> 02:06:12.583
You see things a lot
clearer from the bottom.

1329
02:06:14.250 --> 02:06:16.333
How many suitors are there?

1330
02:06:16.500 --> 02:06:17.583
Dozens.

1331
02:06:18.083 --> 02:06:21.666
- But if his crew is like you...
- He's got no one.

1332
02:06:22.333 --> 02:06:23.750
Are you the only one?

1333
02:06:24.833 --> 02:06:26.166
And you.

1334
02:06:31.750 --> 02:06:33.583
Telemachus is back.
- What?

1335
02:06:33.750 --> 02:06:35.416
Telemachus is back!

1336
02:06:36.083 --> 02:06:38.583
Who said that?
- Everyone!

1337
02:06:38.833 --> 02:06:39.833
Where's Telemachus at?

1338
02:06:40.833 --> 02:06:43.916
My queen. you should
probably stay upstairs!

1339
02:06:51.916 --> 02:06:53.166
Is it for real?

1340
02:06:56.166 --> 02:06:57.500
He's back!

1341
02:06:58.250 --> 02:06:59.333
I'm here.

1342
02:06:59.916 --> 02:07:01.416
let's celebrate tonight.

1343
02:07:02.500 --> 02:07:05.500
If there's even any food
left to celebrate with.

1344
02:07:07.166 --> 02:07:11.333
Don't sweat it. my loyal suitors
will spoil us for your homecoming.

1345
02:07:12.000 --> 02:07:13.666
Glad to see you're in one piece.

1346
02:07:25.583 --> 02:07:27.083
Glad you're feeling better.

1347
02:07:27.416 --> 02:07:29.666
Time to get you
back to the palace.

1348
02:07:33.000 --> 02:07:34.833
What'd you find
out about your dad?

1349
02:07:36.583 --> 02:07:37.750
Nothing.

1350
02:07:38.500 --> 02:07:42.000
Just war stories. nothing
about what happened after Troy.

1351
02:07:42.916 --> 02:07:44.083
My bad. mom.

1352
02:07:45.000 --> 02:07:49.083
In Sparta. they're only talking
about the disaster coming.

1353
02:07:49.583 --> 02:07:53.666
the dark times the Sea People are gonna
unleash. totally trashing Zeus's laws.

1354
02:07:53.916 --> 02:07:55.166
So it's for real.

1355
02:07:55.416 --> 02:07:57.500
our whole vibe is falling apart.

1356
02:07:57.916 --> 02:08:01.000
Menelaus says we're sitting
ducks with no king on the throne.

1357
02:08:01.166 --> 02:08:03.000
so we brainstormed a plan.

1358
02:08:04.333 --> 02:08:05.583
A plan?

1359
02:08:07.583 --> 02:08:09.916
To kick out those suitors.

1360
02:08:12.166 --> 02:08:13.916
you gotta make a move.

1361
02:08:17.500 --> 02:08:19.333
You want me to
get hitched again?

1362
02:08:19.500 --> 02:08:22.333
Then the other guys will
just take each other out

1363
02:08:22.500 --> 02:08:24.583
and I'll only have
one enemy left.

1364
02:08:25.083 --> 02:08:29.416
I'm coming into my own. I'll tell
the elders Odysseus is toast.

1365
02:08:29.750 --> 02:08:32.750
and Menelaus will convince
'em to hand me the throne.

1366
02:08:32.916 --> 02:08:36.583
You're ditching your dad. and I'm walking
out of here with one of these snakes.

1367
02:08:36.750 --> 02:08:38.750
What a plan!
- Come up with something better then.

1368
02:08:42.083 --> 02:08:43.833
Let's lock it all
down. set it ablaze

1369
02:08:44.000 --> 02:08:46.000
and burn these losers!

1370
02:08:46.750 --> 02:08:51.000
You think if I get remarried.
things will just go back to normal.

1371
02:08:51.666 --> 02:08:53.416
This whole world is done.

1372
02:08:53.583 --> 02:08:54.833
And in the next one.

1373
02:08:55.083 --> 02:08:58.000
they aren't giving up
power to you or Odysseus.

1374
02:08:58.166 --> 02:09:00.250
If he shows up. he's gonna
have to wipe them out.

1375
02:09:00.666 --> 02:09:02.250
just like you'll have to.

1376
02:09:02.500 --> 02:09:03.500
If I off them.

1377
02:09:03.666 --> 02:09:06.916
their families will want
payback and I'll be exiled.

1378
02:09:07.500 --> 02:09:09.166
And without me.
the throne is gone.

1379
02:09:09.333 --> 02:09:11.500
Cause only a dude can sit on it.

1380
02:09:12.583 --> 02:09:13.666
"An empty throne"?

1381
02:09:15.416 --> 02:09:18.583
I've been sitting on this
empty throne for twenty years.

1382
02:09:19.000 --> 02:09:21.416
My smarts. my
years of experience

1383
02:09:21.583 --> 02:09:24.500
don't mean squat next to
the hair on your chin.

1384
02:09:26.916 --> 02:09:28.166
You want peace

1385
02:09:28.750 --> 02:09:29.750
or payback?

1386
02:09:29.916 --> 02:09:30.916
You want Odysseus!

1387
02:09:34.500 --> 02:09:35.500
Sing.

1388
02:09:36.166 --> 02:09:37.583
Oh. Muse. a face!

1389
02:09:40.250 --> 02:09:41.250
A face!

1390
02:09:46.083 --> 02:09:47.083
A fleet!

1391
02:09:51.333 --> 02:09:52.416
War!

1392
02:09:56.416 --> 02:09:57.666
In Troy!

1393
02:10:01.500 --> 02:10:03.583
Sing. oh Muse. of a man!

1394
02:10:07.416 --> 02:10:08.416
A man!

1395
02:10:12.500 --> 02:10:13.583
An idea!

1396
02:10:17.333 --> 02:10:18.500
Cunning!

1397
02:10:22.083 --> 02:10:23.750
Eumaeus. go on ahead.

1398
02:10:30.333 --> 02:10:31.333
Argos.

1399
02:10:53.083 --> 02:10:55.166
You're gonna bury
him on the cliff.

1400
02:10:56.916 --> 02:10:58.333
Where you two first met?

1401
02:11:06.500 --> 02:11:08.000
You're Odysseus.

1402
02:11:10.750 --> 02:11:12.166
You're my dad.

1403
02:11:14.750 --> 02:11:16.000
I'm just a beggar.

1404
02:11:19.166 --> 02:11:20.333
And you.

1405
02:11:22.250 --> 02:11:23.583
are the solid.

1406
02:11:24.833 --> 02:11:26.166
awesome son

1407
02:11:26.583 --> 02:11:28.000
of Odysseus.

1408
02:11:29.583 --> 02:11:30.583
A son who.

1409
02:11:31.166 --> 02:11:33.083
when you finally link up.

1410
02:11:35.083 --> 02:11:36.583
is gonna be his pride and joy.

1411
02:11:40.750 --> 02:11:42.083
Welcome home.

1412
02:11:42.500 --> 02:11:43.833
stranger.

1413
02:11:47.000 --> 02:11:49.083
Because the darkness of winning

1414
02:11:50.166 --> 02:11:52.416
hides the people
who tell the stories

1415
02:11:54.250 --> 02:11:57.583
and turns us all into
blind poets and bums!

1416
02:12:04.833 --> 02:12:06.833
Show some hospitality
like Zeus wants.

1417
02:12:07.583 --> 02:12:09.333
Give the stranger some food.

1418
02:12:09.500 --> 02:12:10.583
Nah. boss.

1419
02:12:11.416 --> 02:12:13.750
I'll hit the tables
with my bowl.

1420
02:12:19.166 --> 02:12:21.750
Did you invite some
gross parasite again?

1421
02:12:22.000 --> 02:12:24.166
Just another beggar.

1422
02:12:42.666 --> 02:12:45.333
Let's off him before
he charms the Elders.

1423
02:12:45.500 --> 02:12:46.666
How?

1424
02:13:04.250 --> 02:13:05.416
Call him out.

1425
02:13:05.916 --> 02:13:07.750
make him grab a weapon.

1426
02:13:12.250 --> 02:13:15.083
He ain't our little pup
to mess with anymore.

1427
02:13:15.333 --> 02:13:17.583
So we come back tonight
and take him out.

1428
02:13:19.500 --> 02:13:21.000
Beat it. Please.

1429
02:13:21.916 --> 02:13:24.166
I'm starving.
- Get lost!

1430
02:13:24.333 --> 02:13:27.833
Can't you be generous
with someone else's grub?

1431
02:13:29.750 --> 02:13:31.833
There's no room in your bowl.

1432
02:13:38.583 --> 02:13:39.916
For sure.

1433
02:13:41.250 --> 02:13:42.250
Here.

1434
02:13:46.916 --> 02:13:49.416
You think I've got
something for you?

1435
02:13:50.500 --> 02:13:52.416
Actually. I do have
something for you.

1436
02:13:53.416 --> 02:13:55.083
You've got something for me?

1437
02:13:56.333 --> 02:13:57.833
He's got something for me!

1438
02:13:59.000 --> 02:14:02.250
What could a gross.

1439
02:14:02.500 --> 02:14:03.916
old moocher like you

1440
02:14:04.083 --> 02:14:05.166
possibly have that I'd want?

1441
02:14:05.333 --> 02:14:07.833
Actually. this is yours.

1442
02:14:12.916 --> 02:14:14.666
I was told to give
it back to you.

1443
02:14:16.750 --> 02:14:17.916
It ain't mine.

1444
02:14:19.583 --> 02:14:20.666
Is that so?

1445
02:14:23.833 --> 02:14:25.083
Where'd you find it?

1446
02:14:27.250 --> 02:14:29.166
Don't turn your back on me!

1447
02:14:34.083 --> 02:14:35.166
Antinous.

1448
02:14:35.666 --> 02:14:38.166
Show some respect to beggars.
- That's Zeus's law.

1449
02:14:38.916 --> 02:14:40.083
Zeus's law?

1450
02:14:44.416 --> 02:14:45.750
Is he a god?

1451
02:14:49.166 --> 02:14:51.000
Is he a god in disguise?

1452
02:14:51.750 --> 02:14:52.750
Tell us!

1453
02:14:54.416 --> 02:14:55.583
Are you a god.

1454
02:14:56.750 --> 02:14:57.916
you suck-up?

1455
02:15:00.416 --> 02:15:02.416
I'm a vet from the Trojan War.

1456
02:15:03.000 --> 02:15:05.166
A Trojan War vet.

1457
02:15:07.583 --> 02:15:09.583
What's your name. vet?

1458
02:15:13.083 --> 02:15:14.083
Sinon.

1459
02:15:17.583 --> 02:15:19.500
Does that name ring a bell?

1460
02:15:22.416 --> 02:15:26.000
With it. I honor the
bravest of the young guys.

1461
02:15:26.666 --> 02:15:27.750
Sinon?

1462
02:15:29.333 --> 02:15:31.333
Wasn't he your shepherd's kid?

1463
02:15:33.416 --> 02:15:34.500
Doesn't mean anything to me.

1464
02:15:35.416 --> 02:15:37.333
You tried to replace him.

1465
02:15:37.500 --> 02:15:39.083
Where'd you find this?

1466
02:15:39.250 --> 02:15:40.916
Where you're gonna
be pretty soon.

1467
02:15:41.500 --> 02:15:42.666
Meaning?

1468
02:15:43.416 --> 02:15:44.416
With Hades.

1469
02:15:47.833 --> 02:15:49.000
Enough!

1470
02:15:50.500 --> 02:15:52.166
The party's over!

1471
02:15:56.083 --> 02:15:57.166
Let's go.

1472
02:15:58.500 --> 02:15:59.750
It's not mine!

1473
02:16:08.083 --> 02:16:09.916
The queen wants to
chop it up with you

1474
02:16:10.166 --> 02:16:13.083
once the hall clears out
and the fires are lit.

1475
02:16:59.000 --> 02:17:00.000

1476
1475
02:17:05.500 --> 02:17:06.916
Good evening. traveler.

1477
02:17:08.000 --> 02:17:09.083
My queen.

1478
02:17:09.500 --> 02:17:10.500
Melantho.

1479
02:17:10.750 --> 02:17:13.416
let Eurycleia wash
the stranger's feet.

1480
02:17:13.666 --> 02:17:15.000
No need.

1481
02:17:15.250 --> 02:17:19.416
My husband always insisted on
treating guests like family.

1482
02:17:19.583 --> 02:17:22.000
Have you heard of my
husband. Odysseus?

1483
02:17:22.250 --> 02:17:23.416
For sure.

1484
02:17:23.916 --> 02:17:25.333
From the songs.

1485
02:17:25.750 --> 02:17:27.333
I was at Troy. noble lady.

1486
02:17:28.166 --> 02:17:30.666
The songs must sound
like a joke to you.

1487
02:17:31.750 --> 02:17:33.250
They make me tear up...

1488
02:17:34.416 --> 02:17:35.500
What are you crying about?

1489
02:17:36.166 --> 02:17:37.583
For everything that's gone.

1490
02:17:38.500 --> 02:17:39.666
For the lives lost?

1491
02:17:40.416 --> 02:17:41.916
And for the years.

1492
02:17:43.000 --> 02:17:44.083
and for everything else.

1493
02:17:52.166 --> 02:17:54.333
Did you know Odysseus at Troy?

1494
02:17:54.833 --> 02:17:56.000
Yeah.

1495
02:17:56.916 --> 02:17:59.333
Did you notice anything weird

1496
02:17:59.500 --> 02:18:01.083
about his clothes?

1497
02:18:01.916 --> 02:18:03.916
A strange brooch.

1498
02:18:04.500 --> 02:18:05.583
Strange?

1499
02:18:06.250 --> 02:18:07.250
Beautiful.

1500
02:18:08.083 --> 02:18:09.583
but weird!

1501
02:18:10.000 --> 02:18:11.000
Describe it.

1502
02:18:26.333 --> 02:18:28.000
I'll grab fresh water.

1503
02:18:32.500 --> 02:18:34.083
It was a gorgeous

1504
02:18:34.250 --> 02:18:35.583
gold brooch.

1505
02:18:36.750 --> 02:18:39.750
showing Athena wrapped in vines.

1506
02:18:48.750 --> 02:18:50.500
Did he rock it a lot?

1507
02:18:51.916 --> 02:18:53.250
He never took it off.

1508
02:19:14.666 --> 02:19:17.583
How'd you manage to make
it back. unlike Odysseus?

1509
02:19:18.833 --> 02:19:21.333
I haven't made it back yet.

1510
02:19:22.250 --> 02:19:23.416
Why?

1511
02:19:23.583 --> 02:19:26.500
Getting back home
isn't always a vibe.

1512
02:19:26.833 --> 02:19:29.250
That's true for both
Odysseus and Ios.

1513
02:19:30.583 --> 02:19:32.250
The Odysseus I knew

1514
02:19:33.166 --> 02:19:35.750
would've found a way back to me.

1515
02:19:35.916 --> 02:19:38.083
regardless of the storms.

1516
02:19:38.583 --> 02:19:42.000
What if the Odysseus you
knew is gone for good?

1517
02:19:46.250 --> 02:19:47.333
What if.

1518
02:19:48.416 --> 02:19:49.583
one night.

1519
02:19:50.583 --> 02:19:52.083
in some random city.

1520
02:19:53.750 --> 02:19:55.166
what he saw

1521
02:19:56.333 --> 02:19:59.083
made him realize
the home he knew

1522
02:20:00.083 --> 02:20:02.250
was never coming back?

1523
02:20:05.750 --> 02:20:06.750
What if.

1524
02:20:07.333 --> 02:20:09.250
when he crawled out
of the horse's gut

1525
02:20:13.333 --> 02:20:15.333
and busted open Troy's gates.

1526
02:20:20.333 --> 02:20:22.916
he saw how ten
years of pure rage

1527
02:20:23.583 --> 02:20:25.750
could wreck a whole
city in a single night?

1528
02:21:11.500 --> 02:21:12.583
Come on. everyone!

1529
02:21:12.916 --> 02:21:14.083
Hurry!

1530
02:22:37.916 --> 02:22:39.583
We'd left them

1531
02:22:39.916 --> 02:22:41.000
a gift.

1532
02:22:41.583 --> 02:22:43.750
a peace offering.

1533
02:22:43.916 --> 02:22:45.000
which they took

1534
02:22:45.583 --> 02:22:47.250
straight to their place.

1535
02:22:57.750 --> 02:23:01.000
We totally trashed
what was most sacred

1536
02:23:02.000 --> 02:23:03.583
between people.

1537
02:23:05.416 --> 02:23:06.666
and turned the fight...

1538
02:23:07.666 --> 02:23:08.916
Smash their idols!

1539
02:23:10.916 --> 02:23:12.333
Into a manhunt.

1540
02:23:28.500 --> 02:23:30.583
Burning down Troy's walls

1541
02:23:31.166 --> 02:23:33.833
meant turning the world to dust.

1542
02:23:35.416 --> 02:23:37.083
his own place included.

1543
02:23:44.000 --> 02:23:45.250
And if he knew.

1544
02:23:47.166 --> 02:23:48.666
that night.

1545
02:23:51.750 --> 02:23:53.833
walking through the fires

1546
02:23:54.416 --> 02:23:56.666
of pure chaos and misery...

1547
02:24:46.750 --> 02:24:50.750
And during the parties
after. dripping in sweat.

1548
02:24:56.666 --> 02:24:58.666
if he knew exactly

1549
02:24:59.083 --> 02:25:00.333
what he'd done?

1550
02:25:19.166 --> 02:25:21.000
What you all had done.

1551
02:25:21.166 --> 02:25:22.916
One man's idea.

1552
02:25:24.500 --> 02:25:26.083
one man's scheme.

1553
02:25:27.666 --> 02:25:29.333
to break Zeus's law

1554
02:25:29.500 --> 02:25:30.666
for good.

1555
02:25:31.666 --> 02:25:33.666
We lived in a world
of fancy palaces.

1556
02:25:34.083 --> 02:25:35.250
of trades

1557
02:25:36.750 --> 02:25:37.916
and deals.

1558
02:25:38.166 --> 02:25:40.000
clueless to how good we had it.

1559
02:25:40.833 --> 02:25:42.333
until we smashed it all.

1560
02:25:44.750 --> 02:25:47.333
You're the Sea People.

1561
02:25:49.333 --> 02:25:50.416
Yeah. my queen.

1562
02:25:52.250 --> 02:25:55.333
Ignoring Zeus's law is
spreading like a virus.

1563
02:25:55.583 --> 02:25:57.083
our whole world is tanking.

1564
02:25:57.583 --> 02:26:01.250
Maybe he didn't want to

1565
02:26:01.583 --> 02:26:02.750
see the wreckage of his choices

1566
02:26:02.916 --> 02:26:05.083
anywhere. especially
not back home.

1567
02:26:14.166 --> 02:26:15.333
But Odysseus is still out there

1568
02:26:17.750 --> 02:26:19.750
and will show up when
it really matters.

1569
02:26:21.750 --> 02:26:22.916
Either way.

1570
02:26:24.500 --> 02:26:27.250
I've spent way too long
living in his ruins.

1571
02:26:32.500 --> 02:26:35.583
Invite the suitors at sunrise.
get the weapons ready.

1572
02:26:35.750 --> 02:26:39.750
One suitor's gonna be stoked soon.
and the rest will be out for blood.

1573
02:26:40.333 --> 02:26:42.500
No weapons allowed
for the contest

1574
02:26:42.666 --> 02:26:44.166
and lock the doors.

1575
02:26:44.916 --> 02:26:47.236
I'm marrying whoever
wins my challenge.

1576
02:26:53.750 --> 02:26:55.666
How are we gonna deal with them?

1577
02:26:56.250 --> 02:26:57.416
Not 'we'.

1578
02:26:58.000 --> 02:26:59.916
Their blood is on my hands.

1579
02:27:00.416 --> 02:27:02.250
And you'd risk
getting kicked out.

1580
02:27:02.916 --> 02:27:04.000
And you wouldn't?

1581
02:27:04.833 --> 02:27:06.916
Get the weapons
out of their reach.

1582
02:27:07.083 --> 02:27:08.416
Got it.

1583
02:27:08.833 --> 02:27:11.166
Even without weapons.
there's a ton of them

1584
02:27:11.666 --> 02:27:13.416
and you won't be strapped.

1585
02:27:14.666 --> 02:27:16.083
I'll be strapped.

1586
02:27:17.666 --> 02:27:19.166
Your mom's got it covered.

1587
02:27:21.583 --> 02:27:23.666
Grab some trusted people.

1588
02:27:23.833 --> 02:27:26.000
to stash the weapons upstairs.

1589
02:27:44.250 --> 02:27:46.000
Hurry. put the weapons away.

1590
02:27:54.083 --> 02:27:55.166
Fast.

1591
02:28:17.083 --> 02:28:19.333
Zeus seems pretty invested
in how this goes down.

1592
02:28:19.666 --> 02:28:21.083
But what's the contest?

1593
02:28:44.166 --> 02:28:45.583
For years.

1594
02:28:46.666 --> 02:28:48.583
while my husband's
been ghosting.

1595
02:28:49.250 --> 02:28:52.750
you've taken over this
place for your parties.

1596
02:28:52.916 --> 02:28:56.416
acting like you're
trying to win my hand.

1597
02:28:59.916 --> 02:29:02.000
Listening to you guys partying.

1598
02:29:03.666 --> 02:29:04.833
how you brawl.

1599
02:29:06.500 --> 02:29:08.416
how you bribe my servants

1600
02:29:08.666 --> 02:29:10.916
and trash my house.

1601
02:29:11.083 --> 02:29:15.333
I kept hoping Odysseus would
show up and see all this.

1602
02:29:22.583 --> 02:29:23.833
But last night.

1603
02:29:24.666 --> 02:29:25.666
I realized.

1604
02:29:26.166 --> 02:29:28.166
that since he's still not here.

1605
02:29:31.000 --> 02:29:32.250
he's not coming back.

1606
02:29:34.250 --> 02:29:35.500
That's why.

1607
02:29:36.333 --> 02:29:39.583
I'm ready to marry whoever here.

1608
02:29:39.916 --> 02:29:42.166
can string this hunting bow

1609
02:29:42.333 --> 02:29:45.583
and nail a shot through
these twelve axes.

1610
02:29:47.500 --> 02:29:48.916
Step up.

1611
02:29:50.500 --> 02:29:51.833
show us what you got!

1612
02:29:53.583 --> 02:29:54.666
Eumaeus?

1613
02:30:06.833 --> 02:30:08.250
Who's going first?

1614
02:30:08.500 --> 02:30:10.083
Hand me that bow.

1615
02:30:30.916 --> 02:30:32.166
It's pointless.

1616
02:30:32.416 --> 02:30:33.416
For you.

1617
02:30:33.833 --> 02:30:36.083
When I was a kid. I saw Odysseus
do it like it was nothing.

1618
02:30:36.250 --> 02:30:37.250
Then do it.

1619
02:30:38.166 --> 02:30:39.250
I'm waiting my turn.

1620
02:30:40.583 --> 02:30:43.416
Why don't we warm up
and grease the string?

1621
02:30:44.416 --> 02:30:46.500
It's gotten all
crusty over the years.

1622
02:31:21.416 --> 02:31:22.416
Your turn.

1623
02:31:22.916 --> 02:31:24.000
It's pointless.

1624
02:31:27.250 --> 02:31:28.916
My queen has the final say.

1625
02:31:29.416 --> 02:31:31.000
Odysseus is irreplaceable.

1626
02:31:31.166 --> 02:31:32.833
Some of us always knew that

1627
02:31:33.000 --> 02:31:35.833
and would've followed
that legend to Troy.

1628
02:31:36.083 --> 02:31:37.583
if he'd asked.

1629
02:31:40.083 --> 02:31:41.916
But he didn't make it back.

1630
02:31:43.750 --> 02:31:45.916
so pick the best of us.

1631
02:31:47.083 --> 02:31:49.416
us. who couldn't
handle your test.

1632
02:31:50.000 --> 02:31:51.416
I didn't fail.

1633
02:31:56.333 --> 02:31:58.416
Kick these beggars out!

1634
02:31:59.166 --> 02:32:02.250
Doors are locked until
the contest is over.

1635
02:32:02.500 --> 02:32:04.250
The contest is over.

1636
02:32:05.166 --> 02:32:06.666
I wanna try.

1637
02:32:06.916 --> 02:32:08.333
You're getting on our nerves!

1638
02:32:09.666 --> 02:32:11.583
He's got the right to try.

1639
02:32:12.833 --> 02:32:15.083
If you're bailing on your
turn. let him have it.

1640
02:32:15.666 --> 02:32:17.666
You're disrespecting
your mom's wish.

1641
02:32:17.833 --> 02:32:20.250
Her wish is for
all of you to burn.

1642
02:32:31.666 --> 02:32:34.000
This guy's way too old.

1643
02:32:38.750 --> 02:32:40.750
Let's see this 'pro' in action.

1644
02:32:41.000 --> 02:32:42.083
Moocher!

1645
02:32:44.916 --> 02:32:46.666
Give it up. old man!

1646
02:32:57.750 --> 02:32:58.833
Come on. buddy.

1647
02:32:59.416 --> 02:33:00.416
that's enough.

1648
02:33:00.833 --> 02:33:02.250
Let him try.

1649
02:33:44.333 --> 02:33:45.416
It's you. Odysseus.

1650
02:33:52.166 --> 02:33:54.083
You better stay put.

1651
02:34:06.250 --> 02:34:07.250
Go!

1652
02:34:07.916 --> 02:34:08.916
Is it him?

1653
02:34:09.833 --> 02:34:11.250
It's him!

1654
02:34:20.500 --> 02:34:21.500
Go guard the stash!

1655
02:34:35.833 --> 02:34:38.166
Where are the weapons?
- Upstairs.

1656
02:34:38.416 --> 02:34:39.416
Go grab 'em!

1657
02:34:43.833 --> 02:34:45.250
What are you waiting for?

1658
02:34:45.416 --> 02:34:46.916
He's gonna murk us all.

1659
02:34:50.250 --> 02:34:51.250
Watch out!

1660
02:34:56.333 --> 02:34:59.000
I told you! Too loud. cowherd!

1661
02:35:09.416 --> 02:35:10.416
Yeah!

1662
02:36:15.666 --> 02:36:16.750
Grab the swords!

1663
02:37:15.000 --> 02:37:16.416
Grab the shields!

1664
02:37:54.083 --> 02:37:55.083
The spears!

1665
02:38:24.166 --> 02:38:25.583
Use the spears!

1666
02:39:21.000 --> 02:39:22.583
Thought you were
gonna take us all out?

1667
02:39:23.500 --> 02:39:25.083
Especially you.

1668
02:39:26.250 --> 02:39:27.333
End him.

1669
02:39:30.750 --> 02:39:31.833
Father.

1670
02:40:03.166 --> 02:40:04.166
When you're in Hades.

1671
02:40:06.416 --> 02:40:07.416
tell my people.

1672
02:40:08.000 --> 02:40:10.500
that I'm heading west
to pay my respects.

1673
02:40:16.833 --> 02:40:17.833
And tell Sinon.

1674
02:40:21.083 --> 02:40:23.250
that I got even
for the disrespect.

1675
02:40:43.416 --> 02:40:44.416
And now?

1676
02:40:46.000 --> 02:40:47.333
Did you take 'em down?

1677
02:40:48.583 --> 02:40:50.083
Is he toast?

1678
02:40:51.666 --> 02:40:54.833
We totally wrecked the
trust between people.

1679
02:41:03.583 --> 02:41:06.500
And through the dark
times coming up.

1680
02:41:06.750 --> 02:41:08.500
the stories of Troy

1681
02:41:09.166 --> 02:41:11.333
will just be songs.

1682
02:42:31.750 --> 02:42:33.583
Odysseus. babe!

1683
02:42:37.833 --> 02:42:38.833
Odysseus.

1684
02:42:39.583 --> 02:42:40.750
my love.

1685
02:42:41.333 --> 02:42:42.500
you're back.

1686
02:42:43.833 --> 02:42:45.000
Finally.

1687
02:42:45.500 --> 02:42:46.916
in the last stretch

1688
02:42:48.333 --> 02:42:50.416
to see my sweet Ithaca

1689
02:42:51.333 --> 02:42:52.583
one last time.

1690
02:42:55.000 --> 02:42:56.333
You don't get to do that.

1691
02:42:56.583 --> 02:42:59.000
No. please. I waited forever.

1692
02:43:01.666 --> 02:43:03.416
You don't get to die!

1693
02:43:04.166 --> 02:43:05.250
Not dying.

1694
02:43:07.666 --> 02:43:08.750
exile.

1695
02:43:16.833 --> 02:43:18.583
Telemachus is gonna be king.

1696
02:43:22.416 --> 02:43:24.166
We're heading to
the unknown west

1697
02:43:25.166 --> 02:43:26.833
to honor my people

1698
02:43:28.333 --> 02:43:29.583
together.

1699
02:43:30.083 --> 02:43:32.166
With your fastest boat.

1700
02:43:32.666 --> 02:43:34.250
with your best crew.

1701
02:43:34.833 --> 02:43:36.750
we're chasing the horizon.

1702
02:43:37.750 --> 02:43:39.750
Chasing the sun.

1703
02:43:42.250 --> 02:43:45.000
Why will these
stories only be sung?

1704
02:43:47.166 --> 02:43:51.166
Only songs will keep the memory
of those who could write.

1705
02:43:55.750 --> 02:43:57.833
Society's gonna reset.

1706
02:44:04.083 --> 02:44:06.666
A new day's gonna light
up this dark world.

1707
02:44:10.416 --> 02:44:12.583
and we'll end up forgetting
our mistakes all over again.

1709
02:44:13.305 --> 02:45:13.634
